title: my easiest and best pineapple frosting
directions: Mix it all together and cook 20 minutes on low until thick enough to spread.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Adjust ingredients for more chicken.
Combine and stir first 6 ingredients.
Place chicken breasts in low casserole baking dish. Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 2 people.

title: quick french onion soup
directions: Prepare soup per package directions.
Slowly add grated cheese, stirring to melt cheese.
Add the egg slowly, stirring well.
Remove from heat and pour into 4 soup bowls.
Top with slice of cheese and bread.
Place under broiler until browned and cheese is melted.

title: company coleslaw
directions: Mix cornbread with remaining ingredients. Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: eggnog cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Blend at low speed for 30 seconds, scraping sides and bottom of bowl.
Pour into 2 greased and floured round 8-inch layer pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add 2 tablespoons flour to beef and onion.
Add chili beans, tomato juice, chili powder and enough water to make juice.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: "aunt" tommy's chicken soup
directions: Combine olive oil and onion.
Saute until golden brown.
Add garlic and stir 3 minutes.
Add carrots, celery, water chestnuts, basil and pepper flakes.
Stir another 5 minutes.
Mix in mushrooms, red pepper flakes and potatoes.
Add chicken broth and hoisin sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine shrimp, crab meat, water chestnuts and pimiento in a large mixing bowl.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in medium size saucepan.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms.
Saute gently 5 minutes or until tender.
Add vegetables to seafood mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in same saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt. Cook 1 minute.
Remove pan from heat.
Stir in sherry and cream gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens slightly and comes to boiling.
Add to vegetable-seafood mixture.
Stir in noodles.
Spoon into lightly buttered 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
To use immediately, bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except margarine. Beat at medium speed until batter is smooth.
Stir in margarine.

title: frozen strawberry preserves
directions: Clean berries; wash and drain.
Crush with potato masher.
Add 1 cup of water to 1 box Sure-Jell.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute. Pour over berries and sugar; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pack into containers and place in deep freeze after chilling in refrigerator.

title: snickerdoodles (cookies)
directions: Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: orange pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, oleo and sugar; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mash down hard to make crust.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.
Cool. Blend package cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Carefully pour mixture onto pretzel crust.
Chill.
Mix Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Drain juice from pineapple and add water to make 1 cup liquid.
Add to Jell-O and chill, then add pineapple. Chill until slightly thickened, then pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: gram's crumb cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together like pie dough.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk.
Blend into mixture. Pour into a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved mixture evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: joanne's pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook to soft ball stage and add 1/3 stick butter.
Beat and then add 1 cup pecans.

title: oxtail soup(copyright 1908 - 1933)
directions: Melt fat and fry in it the carrot and onion, cut into dices; also add the oxtails which have been cut in pieces.
When brown, add water, celery, parsley and bay leaf, tied together.
When boiling, put in the barley and simmer 4 hours.
Remove large bones, celery, parsley and bay leaf and thicken the soup with flour, rubbed smooth with 2 tablespoons of cold water.
Season rather highly.
Add sherry flavoring and serve.

title: hawaiian style baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: kit kat bars
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil and boil for 5 minutes. Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: no bake sugar free cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a medium bowl, combine graham crackers, butter and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Press into bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 8-10 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to cool.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Let cool until thickened, but not set.

title: peanut and pretzel bark
directions: Melt candy coating and stir in pretzels and peanuts.
Spread in a thin layer on foil covered baking sheets.
Chill 30 minutes. Break in pieces and store in refrigerator or room temperature. Makes 2 1/2 lb.

title: chinese beets
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until mixture thickens.
Serve warm.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: cranberry pear chutney
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large pan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmer.
Continue cooking for about 30 to 40 minutes or until cranberries are tender and the mixture has thickened.
Makes about 1 1/2 pints.

title: broccoli cheese soup(for a crowd)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in soup pot. Simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and heat, but do not boil.

title: dirt
directions: Mix the powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese and set aside. Add the milk to the pudding. Add the first mixture and fold into the Cool Whip. Layer the white mixture and alternate with the Oreos. Can top with anything desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover chicken breasts with water.
Add rosemary leaves and celery; boil until tender.
Save broth.

title: mother's tomato soup cake
directions: Sift flour with soda, cinnamon and cloves in a small bowl. Cream butter gradually with sugar and flour.
Add dry ingredients, then soup, raisins and nuts.
Rinse soup can with 1/4 cup of water and add last.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour.
Use a cream cheese frosting.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix well and divide into 3 or 4 parts.
Form into long roll and let stand until hard (refrigerator).
Slice into thin slices; bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan while warm to avoid breaking.
Will keep indefinitely.
I like keeping rolls in freezer to bake as needed.
Been making (mother's helper) since 10 years old.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Brown sausage in olive oil; set aside.
Lightly saute bell peppers and onion in the same pan.
Cut sausage into bite-size pieces.
Return to pan; mix with peppers and onion.
Can be served over rice or as an hors d'oeuvre.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Pull meat into large pieces.
Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Put broccoli into buttered pan. Arrange chicken over this.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix sauce and soups together and heat.
Brown beef; drain. Grease a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Break tortillas into four pieces. Layer tortillas, meat, sauce, cheese, etc., ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tomato butter
directions: Blanch, peel and cut tomatoes into quarters.
Place in a large kettle and simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, until soft and mushy.
Measure tomatoes.
There should be about 6 cups.
Put back into kettle with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer uncovered, stirring frequently, until thick, about 45 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour into hot sterilized jars. Seal immediately.
Makes about four 8 ounce jars.

title: sheepherder's meat loaf(yields 12 portions)
directions: In bowl, mix eggs, bread crumbs, garlic, lemon juice and herbs.
Add mixture to ground lamb and mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Form into loaf on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until
juices run clear.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in skins.
Peel and mash.
Mix sugar and butter in potatoes while hot.
Beat in eggs, milk, flour and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm.

title: stir 'n roll biscuits("regular")
directions: Combine dry ingredients into bowl.
Measure oil and milk together in a cup. Pour the milk and oil into flour mixture. Stir with fork until mixture cleans bowl and forms a ball.
Knead dough until it looks smooth.
Pat or roll dough out on wax paper.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: carolina brown rice and chicken
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix rice, chopped onion and mushrooms in dish.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Pour over rice mixture (lay chicken parts on top of rice first).
Lay stick of margarine (sliced up) on top chicken.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sirloin tip roast
directions: Wipe roast with damp cloth.
Sprinkle garlic salt over entire surface.
Add sauces to top of roast.
Wrap in aluminum foil using double folds to seal.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: spaghetti casserole(4 servings)
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
Brown in a 9 or 10-inch skillet (or any oven-safe skillet).
Drain all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Stir in onion, green peppers and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.

title: super duper french toast
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add orange juice, water, milk, sugar, vanilla, salt and peel and mix well.
Dip bread into egg mixture, turning to coat all surfaces.
Transfer to baking dish in single layer.

title: panettone bread and butter pudding
directions: To start custard base, bring milk and cream just to a boil in a saucepan. Cut the vanilla pod in half, (I use vanilla extract, 1 1/2 Tbsp.) scrape out the seeds and add to the pan with the zest. Whisk the eggs with the sugar until pale. Add the milk and cream and remove the vanilla pod. Preheat oven to 325°. Butter each slice of bread and dip into the custard and pile into a buttered baking dish. Pour the remaining custard slowly over the bread. Place the dish in a roasting pan and fill halfway with hot water. Sprinkle pudding with confectioners sugar and bake for about 45-50 minutes. When cooked, it will have a slight crust on top, but will still be slightly wobbly inside.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in covered container.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Put all ingredients in one bowl and stir until just mixed. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, mixed fruit and peaches, reserving pineapple juice.
Combine juice, pudding mix and instant breakfast drink; stir well.
Combine fruit and dressing; toss gently.
Chill. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Soak the apples and sugar together for 1 hour.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add the pecans to the dry ingredients. Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour or until done at 350° (325° if in glass pans).
Makes 2 loaves or 1 tube cake.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Chop celery and onion and add to stuffing mix.
Add chicken broth, chicken soup (undiluted) and oleo. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until celery and onion are done and casserole is slightly browned.

title: sammy's special stew
directions: Put green beans and hot wings in a large pot.
Bring to boil. Turn to simmer.
Cook about an hour.
Add onions.
Continue to simmer until chicken is tender.
This is a great meal on a cold winter day.

title: red skin potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into chunks and steam or boil until begin to get soft, but not mushy.
Leave skins on or peel if desired.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Heat oil in a saucepan.
Cook onions, celery and mushrooms in it for 3 minutes.
Add 1 cup of chicken stock, soy sauce and chicken; cook 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with remaining chicken stock and stir into chicken mixture until thickened.
Add the scallions.
Serve over chow mein noodles which have been crisped in oven and white rice on side.

title: sponge cake(never fail)
directions: Beat 5 egg yolks and water until thick and lemon colored. Fold in sugar, salt, vanilla, flour, baking powder and last, stiffly beaten egg whites with cream of tartar.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
A very nice cake.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
Freezes well before baking.

title: baby ruth candy bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Mix together. Spread over top of Rice Krispies mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bubble coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt cake pan.
Place frozen dinner rolls all around pan.
Mix together cinnamon and sugar.
Roll all rolls completely in mixture.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding and the chopped pecans over the rolls.
Then pour the cup of butter over top.
Cover with wax paper.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place cooked broccoli in shallow dish.
Top with sliced chicken.
Combine chicken soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops in mushroom sauce
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Coat well with flour.
In a skillet heat oil and brown chops on both sides.
Remove chops & place on platter.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Stir well to mix all ingredients in skillet together.
When this mixture comes to a boil add pork chops.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, and Worcestershire Sauce.
Serve with cookjed rice or mashed potatoes.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown beef, pour off oil from beef.
Mix with chili and soup. Bring to simmer.
Put a tablespoon or so of water if you think you need it.
Put in layer of Fritos, meat mixture and cheese until dish is full.
Put Fritos and cheese on top.

title: heavenly turkey macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Meanwhile, in a large salad bowl, combine mayonnaise, cream, celery, scallions, ginger, salt and pepper.
Add macaroni, turkey, grapes and walnuts; mix lightly. Serve on greens.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy kisses, in a large mixer bowl.
Mix on lowest speed.
Shape the dough into balls.
Roll in sugar. Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove and top with candy kiss.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix well the cake mix and pudding. Add milk, eggs and shortening. Beat 2 minutes. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Poke holes in warm cake. Mix orange juice with powdered sugar. Spread on warm cake. Set aside to cool.

title: log house chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole.
Top with half package of stuffing mix, 1 stick butter or oleo, melted.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chinese almond cakes
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients into large bowl.
Blend in lard with pastry cutter.
Beat together and add remaining ingredients.
Mix as you would pastry and when thoroughly blended, form into balls about the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet and press with heel of your hand to flatten.
Press 1 whole blanched almond into the top of each cookie and brush cookie with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 36 cookies.
Enjoy.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: In 10-inch skillet or wok, heat oil.
Add raw vegetables and stir-fry until tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
In small bowl, combine water, teriyaki sauce, sherry, broth mix and cornstarch, stirring to dissolve broth mix and cornstarch.
Add to vegetables and stir to combine thoroughly.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken, reduce heat and let simmer until thoroughly heated.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel oranges and grapefruit and divide.
Combine with pineapple and nuts, peaches and/or strawberries.
Combine ingredients and serve on lettuce.
Garnish with cherries.

title: chocolate covered worms
directions: Melt the packages of chips in the top of a double boiler.
Add noodles to melted mixture.
Stir carefully with a wooden spoon until noodles are completely coated.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.
Kids will love them.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and clean mushroom ribs.
Chop.
Add onion and saute for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add crumbs and enough milk needed to keep mixture together.
Add cheese; stuff mushroom caps.
Line baking pan with foil.
Arrange mushrooms in pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: instant cocoa with marshmallows
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Store in an airtight container.
To make hot cocoa, combine 1/2 cup mix with 1 1/8 cups of boiling water.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips and almonds.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with chips and almonds.
Refrigerate overnight or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southern buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Turn into a medium bowl.
Cut in shortening until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add buttermilk and stir just until dough holds together.
A little more buttermilk may be needed.
Turn onto floured board and knead lightly until dough is smooth.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into rounds.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes or until golden. Makes 12 biscuits.

title: pistachio dream
directions: Mix crumbs, margarine and nuts. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool. Meanwhile, mix 1 cup Cool Whip with cream cheese and sugar. Spread on top of crumbs. Mix pudding and milk. Spread over cream cheese mixture. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: pineapple sauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat in 2 egg yolks and extracts. Stir soda into pineapple and add to mixture.
Add flour and baking powder.
Add salt to egg whites.
Beat well and fold.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: icebox cheese cake
directions: Make graham cracker crust and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Refrigerate until quivery stage.
Cream the 2 packages of cream cheese with the sugar, vanilla and dash of salt.
Gradually add jello, then fold in the drained, crushed pineapple.
Fold 2 cups Cool Whip into mixture. Put into pan and refrigerate.

title: liver dumplings
directions: Using a blender, chop or grind liver.
Combine crumbs and liquid.
Add slightly beaten eggs and other ingredients.
Shape into small balls the size of large marbles.
Drop into boiling soup or broth.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: bacon deviled eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs.
Mix egg yolks and all ingredients together. Place mixture back into egg halves and serve chilled.

title: doritos chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Layer chicken, chips, cheese and corn, drained, in casserole dish.
Mix soups, milk and tomatoes together.
Pour over casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Color of jello will determine color of cake.
Grease and flour an angel food cake pan.
Beat batter with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not turn cake over.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, 3/4 of the tomato sauce, egg, 3/4 tsp. oregano, salt & pepper.
After mixed pat mixture on a piece of wax paper into a rectangle about 1/2 inch thick. Sprinkle with the Mozzarella cheese.
Roll up starting on short side by lifting the paper slightly.
Continue lifting and peeling to finish the roll.
Seal the edges and place in a loaf pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.
Combine the remaining 1/4 of the sauce & oregano and pour over loaf 15 minutes prior to being done.

title: "veggie" pizza
directions: *Substitute 1 can (4 ounces) mushroom stems and pieces for the fresh mushrooms.

title: steph's chicken soup
directions: Boil thighs with 1 teaspoon salt and bay leaf in soup pot until done.
Debone and chop chicken and add back to soup pot.
Add 3 or 4 drumstick bones back to soup pot (adds flavor).
Add brown rice and simmer 30 minutes.
Add celery, carrots, green beans and stewed tomatoes.
Simmer 15 minutes more.
Add seasonings; stir.
Remove from heat and let sit 10 minutes.
Stir and serve.
Fabulous on a cold winter day with a fresh loaf of bread!

title: aunt fay's dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Spread, in this order: applesauce, pineapple, yellow cake mix, nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and drizzle over.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: whole wheat bread(sammalt hvete brod)
directions: Dissolve sugar and yeast in potato water.
Set aside.

title: meat and cheese loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Mix well.
Pack into a lightly greased 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: Mix all together well.

title: white cloud candy
directions: Combine the Marshmallow Creme, margarine, vanilla and salt. Blend in sugar and nuts.
Press into 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Yields 1 pound and 4 ounces.

title: bible cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients as usual for other cakes. Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate zucchini muffins
directions: Mix together ingredients, except last 4.
Mix last 4 separately and then add to dry ingredients.
Preheat oven to 425°. Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.
(Don't overbake.)

title: egg flower soup
directions: Combine chicken broth, peas and salt.
Simmer until peas are tender, about 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Increase heat to a boil. Slowly pour egg into soup.
Stir gently.
Season with Accent and pepper.

title: turkey noodle bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, including 1 cup chow mein noodles in a 2-quart glass casserole.
Mix well.
Cover with glass lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on Reheat for 8 to 10 minutes or until hot.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Sprinkle top with remaining noodles and serve.

title: low-fat chocolate cake
directions: Dump in a 9 x 13-inch pan and mix with fork.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fran's speedie marinating sauce
directions: Measure everything into a gallon size Ziploc bag set in a large bowl or pan.
Place it into the refrigerator, bowl and all. May marinate chicken up to two days.

title: special cheese cake
directions: Reserve one cup of cake mix.
In a large bowl, combine rest of mix, one egg and oil.
Mixture will be crumbly.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, press it out evenly over bottom and 3/4 up sides of pan.
In same bowl, blend cheese and sugar.
Add remaining 3 eggs and 1 cup of reserved cake mix.
Beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
At slow speed, blend in milk, lemon juice and vanilla. Mix until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust and bake 45 to 55 minutes at 300° until center is firm.
Spread desired pie filling on top.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender.
Alternate layers of carrots, green pepper, and onion in dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, adding more salt if desired,
Beat until well blended.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Serves warm or cold.
Serves 12-15.

title: knox blox(finger jell-o)
directions: In medium bowl, combine Knox and fruit flavored gelatin.
Add boiling water and stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes about 6 dozen.
Coat baking pan with Pam first for easy removal of finger Jell-O.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted comes out clean, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: angel treat
directions: Crumble cake in large bowl.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
In a separate bowl, beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Fold in prepared Dream Whip and crumbled cake.
Pour into flat cake pan.
Spread pie filling over top.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine in large bowl.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour with baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Blend into cream mixture.
Cover; chill for 2 hours. Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll out dough on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 6 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: In mixing bowl dissolve yeast in water.
Add salt and about half the flour, until smooth.
Cover with a damp cloth; place in refrigerator.
Punch down occasionally.
As dough rises about 2 hours before baking cut off amount needed.
Shape in balls in muffin pan.
Let rise until light (2 hours).
Heat oven to 400°. Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: amaretto
directions: Boil sugar, water and lemon juice slow for 1 hour; then remove and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a dark bottle and let sit for 2 weeks.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream sugars, margarine and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients. Add remainder of ingredients.
Drop large tablespoonfuls of dough onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: graham cracker creme pie
directions: Mix.
Place 1/2 in bottom of pie plate.
Set 1/2 aside.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix flour, milk and soup.
Pour over chicken in baking dish. Put in chopped, boiled eggs and chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Place olive oil in saucepan.
Add onion and garlic; brown slightly.
Add tomatoes, basil leaves, salt, pepper and tomato paste; simmer for 2 hours.

title: extra special chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Put 3 bouillon cubes in boiling water (works better if you crushed them in a baggie first); add to melted butter in pan.
Add chopped onion and pepper; add rice and then blend in the soup.
Put seasoned chicken pieces on top and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Press into casserole loaf pan.
Brush 2 tablespoons catsup over top of meatloaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with raw vegetables or hollowed out round loaves of bread.

title: walnut rhubarb bread
directions: Before cooking bread, combine 1 tablespoon melted butter with 1/3 cup white sugar; spread on bread dough (with fingers) before cooking and it will make a crunchy top.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Mix catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, minced onion and barbecue seasoning in a small skillet.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 10 minutes.
Brush on 2 1/2 pounds of chicken during the last 15 minutes of grilling.

title: crab and swiss cheese appetizers
directions: Combine and mix well crab meat, mayonnaise, Swiss cheese, onion and curry powder.
Cut each flaky biscuit horziontally into 3 slices; spread mixture on each slice of biscuit.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: instant hot cocoa
directions: Mix together.
Store in an airtight canister.

title: dill crackers
directions: Put crackers into a 1 gallon jar.
Stir mixture together well. Pour over crackers; put lid on and roll crackers until liquid is absorbed.
Crackers will not be oily.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Dice tomatoes, peppers and cucumbers.
Mix with cooked spaghetti, Salad Supreme and Italian dressing.
Marinate overnight.
Dressing will go to the bottom so mix well before serving.

title: no sugar fruit cookies(for diabetics)
directions: Mix flour and soda, also sweetener if using dry sweetener. Add beaten eggs, then rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cookies will be soft.

title: asparagus soup
directions: Cut the tips off the cooked asparagus and set aside.
Combine the rest of the asparagus; cut in pieces, with the onion, chicken stock and asparagus water.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Strain this mixture by rubbing through a sieve.
Melt the butter; stir in the flour and blend.
Add the milk and seasonings to taste.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add the strained broth and asparagus tips.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: chicken potato bake
directions: Place chicken in greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Arrange potatoes around chicken.
Drizzle with dressing.
Sprinkle italian seasoning and parmesan cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 400 for 20 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20-30 minutes longer until potatoes are tender and chicken juices run clear.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Crumble sausage in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain fat well.
Spread bread cubes in buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Top with sausage and cheese; combine eggs, milk and seasoning.
Beat well.
Pour over cheese and sausage.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Remove and bake for 30 or 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; arrange in casserole dish.
Boil chicken for 20 minutes; place chicken over broccoli.
Mix together the cheese, soup, and Miracle Whip; pour over casserole.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: ol' fashion farm fry
directions: Fry sausage, cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Add cubed potatoes and chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Fry until potatoes are golden, then sprinkle with cheese and add eggs on top of mixture.
Stir over low heat until eggs are cooled.
Serves 4.

title: snowflakes
directions: Melt almond bark; crush Bugles and then put all three ingredients together.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Keep in airtight container.

title: poor man's stew
directions: Cook onion and ground beef in large pot.
Pour all cans of food into pot.
Season to taste with Worcestershire sauce.
Heat and eat!

title: jo's breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain and set aside.
Butter split muffins and lay buttered side down in a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with chilies, Swiss cheese and half of sausage.
Combine eggs and sour cream and pour over top with remaining sausage and Cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator.
Let stand for 1/2 hour. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: take-along crunch cookies
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar.
Blend in egg, milk and vanilla.
Add combined remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on sheet; remove to cooling rack. Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup water; drain and set aside.
Saute onion in oleo until wilted.
Add soup.
Melt cheese in hot mixture.
Add salt, pepper, Accent, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms.
Stir in broccoli.
Sprinkle almonds over top.
Serve warm with chips or party crackers.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until starts to thicken.
Add beaten egg yolks and vanilla.
Cook until thickens.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with meringue or whipped topping.
Cool and serve.

title: cheerwine punch
directions: Make ice
rings
with
1 bottle of Sprite or 7-Up. Fill ring about 3/4 full.
Should make 2 rings.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Stir together apples, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Melt margarine in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk. Pour on top of margarine. Do not stir. Place apples on top of batter and press down into batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: navy bean pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook beans well; drain and mash through colander or food mill.
Measure the mashed beans and add sugar and milk.
Strain this mixture through a sieve.
Add egg yolks, nutmeg, flour, butter and vanilla.
Mix well and beat until very smooth; pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds oven bag (small).

title: shake pickle(icebox)
directions: Fill gallon jar with cukes and sliced onions.
Layer cukes and onions.
Fill jar tight.
Keep pressing down as you fill jar.
Mix the ingredients.
Pour over cukes and onions.
Place jar in refrigerator and shake once a day for 8 days.
Just turn the jar up and down or roll the jar over and over or do both for 8 days. Now ready to eat.
Will keep a long time in jar in refrigerator.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time; beating after each one.
Add milk and vanilla, mix well. Then with spoon, stir in crushed wafers, nuts and coconut.
Bake 1 hour in a loaf or tube pan.

title: chili
directions: Fry meats; drain.
Fry with garlic and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Great for picnics!

title: freezer french toast
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and nutmeg.
Place bread on a jelly roll pan.
Pour egg mixture over bread and let stand a few minutes; turn slices and let stand until absorbed. Place in freezer, uncovered, until firm; transfer to freezer bag and return to freezer.

title: stephanie's holiday surprise
directions: Empty package of pistachio pudding mix.
Add crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Stir in marshmallows, nuts and cherries.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar; set aside.
Melt margarine in heavy saucepan.
Blend in flour while cooking, but do not let mixture brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir cocoa-sugar mixture into this, blending well.
Gradually pour in milk, while stirring, add vanilla.
When smooth, return to heat and cook for about 3 to 4 minutes, still stirring until mixture thickens somewhat.
Remove from heat.
Serve over hot biscuits, sweet rolls, etc.
This is an old-time treat.

title: deluxe jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and let stand 10 minutes. Mix relish, pineapple and nuts; then add to gelatin and mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until set.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread topping on set mixture.
Can be dessert.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn and nuts and mix well.
Turn into 2 large shallow pans.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool. Break apart and store in airtight container.

title: liver casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut liver into bite size chunks.
Coat with flour; place in uncovered baking pan with 1/3 cup melted shortening.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown in oven about 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in remaining shortening in frying pan.
Cook until onion is clear.
Stir in 3 tablespoons flour; add 1 cup water, tomatoes and barbecue sauce.
Cook until thickened.
Drain liver. Place in casserole and pour sauce mixture over liver.
Cover and return to oven.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake about 30 minutes. Serves 5 or 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: manner's strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until clear.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir well.
Set aside until cool but not set solid.
Add fresh strawberries and pour into baked pie shell. Refrigerate several hours.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: kathy's oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda. Cream shortening and sugars (brown and granulated).
Add egg and water; beat in vanilla.
Add sifted flour mixture and oats.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheets; bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: not sweet punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and water.
Add juices; stir.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: caramel nuts
directions: Arrange nuts in clusters.
Place caramels in pan with butter. Heat until melted.
Add vanilla.
Drop onto nut clusters.
Melt chocolate with shortening until hot.
Spread over caramel on clusters.

title: golden cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased mold and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: ranch pea salad
directions: Add Ranch dressing or mix until well coated.

title: spaghetti and meat casserole
directions: Cook meat slightly.
Pour off grease.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to blend.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish. Place grated cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl in order.
Drop by tablespoons and flatten. Six to a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: country apple pie crust
directions: Put flour and salt in a bowl. Blend in all the shortening using a pastry blender. Work quickly so the cold shortening does not melt. It will form a crumbly mixture with pieces the size of peas. Add the cold water and blend. Roll out half of the dough on a floured board. Fold the rolled dough in half and place in a 9-inch pie pan. Unfold and press gently to cover the pan. Cut off excess. Reserve second half of dough to roll and form pie top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water.
Pull meat from bone.
Place in long casserole dish.
Pour cream of chicken soup over chicken. Sprinkle dressing mix over this.
Mix melted butter, beaten eggs and chicken broth.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° until brown and thickened.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar 5 minutes and cool.
Add onions, mango, celery, sauerkraut and bean sprouts.
Chill overnight.
Keeps well.

title: wilma's cracker snacks(microwave)
directions: Wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around each cracker.
Place on paper towels and microwave until bacon is crisp.
Cool and serve.

title: tiramisu cake
directions: Chill a medium sized bowl and beaters.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion with ground beef.
Add other ingredients and simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Add chili powder to taste.

title: honey mustard salad dressing
directions: Heat vinegar and honey in small heavy saucepan over low heat. Stir until honey dissolves.
Pour into bowl and cool.
Whisk in mayonnaise, mustard, onion, parsley and salt.
Gradually whisk in oil.
Can be made 3 days in advance.
Cover and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature and serve.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter crackles
directions: In small bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl, with mixer at medium speed, beat together margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in 1 cup sugar until blended.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Reduce speed to low.
Add flour mixture and beat well.
If necessary, chill dough.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together using a spoon or fork instead of mixer.
Pour into a slightly baked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Sometimes it bakes in 40 minutes.
This can be baked and frozen for later use.

title: pork chop onion-rice bake
directions: Brown chops in lard or drippings.
Spread rice in bottom of rectangular baking dish (13 1/2 x 9 x 2-inch).
Reserve 1 tablespoon of seasoning from envelope of onion soup mix and sprinkle remaining seasoning and bits of onion over rice.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Distribute mushrooms and pimento over rice.
Add hot water to reserved mushroom liquid to total 3 cups liquid and pour over rice.
Arrange browned chops on top of rice mixture and sprinkle chops with reserved seasonings.

title: white buttermilk cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add butter, Crisco, flavoring and 3/4 cup buttermilk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining buttermilk and egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Use two 9-inch pans.
Ice with 7-Minute Frosting or your choice, but cover with coconut.

title: no knead rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water in cup. Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour and beat well.
Beat in yeast and 1 egg, slightly beaten.
Gradually add remaining 2 1/2 cups flour to the soft dough, beating well. Cover and let rise until double.
Oil your hands and shape into balls.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: claude dodson's cornbread
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons shortening in iron skillet.
Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg softly into center of mix.
Pour in buttermilk and mix well.
Pour into hot skillet.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: apricot salad mold
directions: Heat crushed pineapple with sugar.
Mix Jell-O powder into hot pineapple.
Soften cream cheese and mix into apricot nectar.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Add carrots and pecans.
Fold into Cool Whip.
Mold in Bundt pan or mold of your choice.
Freeze.

title: whipped apple cream
directions: Mix together and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: gumdrop gems
directions: Thoroughly cream the butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla; beat in egg.
Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt. Gradually stir into creamed mixture; mix well.
Shape dough into rolls 2 inches in diameter and 12 inches long.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill several hours or overnight.
Cut 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate tops with gumdrop slices.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.
(Remove black candies.)

title: mama's spicy baked beans
directions: Cover beans with ample water and soak overnight.
Simmer over low heat 1 hour.
Mix remaining ingredients and stir into beans. Transfer mixture into bean pot.
Bury pork in beans.
Add boiling water to cover beans.
Cover with lid and bake in slow oven at 300° for 6 hours.
During last hour, remove lid and allow beans to brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and margarine.
Mix thoroughly. Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large mixer bowl place confectioners sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 20 minutes.
Don't underbeat.
Spread mixture over graham cracker crust.
Spread pineapple over creamed mixture.

title: never fail pecan pie
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Add
vanilla,
corn
syrup and cornstarch.	Pour into a 9-inch pie
shell.
Cover with 1 cup of pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: consomme pork chops
directions: Spray 14 x 9-inch dish with Pam.
Put in raw rice, consomme, drained mushrooms, parsley, garlic and onion juice.
Stir.
Brown pork chops in oil after seasoning with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place undrained pork chops on rice mixture.
Place bell pepper rings on top of pork chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 325° oven.
Serves 4 to 8 according to number of chops per person.
Can be assembled and refrigerated for a day prior to baking.

title: grandma's spanish zucchini
directions: In a large pot place zucchini, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Place on high, heat, cover and bring to boil. Turn down to low heat and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Add cheese and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except meat.
Add the meat; mix and shape into a loaf and place in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: "hall's banana nut bread"
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, shortening and vanilla extract until smooth. Add flour, soda, salt and overripe bananas.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in two greased and floured loaf pans at 350° to 375° for one hour or until done.
Add some nuts on the top before baking.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat in salad oil with onion until brown.
In saucepan, prepare sauce mix and 6 cups water with mushroom soup.*
Simmer 15 minutes.
Layer tortillas in large casserole dish and rotate layers of meat, sauce mix, tortillas and cheese for 3 layers. Pour remaining sauce over top and spread remaining cheese.
Cook 45minutes at 350° with cover, then remove cover and cook an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin bars(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
With electric mixer, combine margarine, apple juice concentrate, fructose and mashed banana.
Beat in egg, pumpkin and vanilla.
Stir flour, cinnamon, ginger, allspice and baking soda in a medium bowl until blended.
Stir dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating. Bake for 25 minutes or until firm in center.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix well all ingredients, except potatoes, then add potatoes; mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: fettuccine carbonara with spring vegetables
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Cut ham into 1/2 inch wide strips.
Cut carrots into very thin rounds.
In a small bowl, beat the eggs, Parmesan and pepper together.
Add fettuccine to boiling water and cook until almost done, 8 to 10 minutes.
Add carrots and peas and cook the pasta and vegetables for 2 minutes, or until the pasta is al dente and the carrots are crisp.
Drain the pasta and spaghetti into the colander, letting the boiling water heat the bowl.
Pour water out of bowl.
Add the drained hot pasta and vegetables.
Pour beaten egg mixture over the hot pasta and toss to cook eggs and coat the pasta.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Blend all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs in serving size pieces.
Brown slowly in two 10-inch skillets (better if browned in iron skillet); put in baking pan.
Pour fat from skillet and melt butter in skillet; add onion.
Cook until brown.
Add next 8 ingredients; simmer 20 minutes.
Set oven for 350°.
Pour sauce over ribs and bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.

title: onion soup
directions: Slice onions and saute until light brown; add flour, mustard and seasonings.
Carefully add water or broth.
Simmer for at least 1 1/2 to 2 hours or more.
To serve, place soup in bowls; add slices of bread and cheese.
Microwave each serving until cheese melts.

title: busy day chicken casserole
directions: Place uncooked rice in a well-greased loaf cake pan or large casserole.
Salt and pepper the chicken pieces and arrange chicken on top of the rice.
Dot well with small pieces of butter. Sprinkle the dry onion soup over the chicken and then pour boiling water over all the ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hot spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach; squeeze out all water.
Combine all ingredients. Chill for 2 hours.
Roll mixture into 2-inch bite size balls.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour or microwave on High 4 to 7 minutes.

title: vegetable cheese linguine
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add mushrooms and green onions; saute 3 minutes.
Add spinach, tomatoes, parsley and chicken broth; cook 1 minute.
Set aside and keep warm.
Cook pasta according to package directions, omitting salt and fat; drain.
Place pasta in a large bowl; add cheese, tossing gently.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 2 servings (240 calories per 2 cup serving).

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix well or use mixer. Blend sweet potatoes, milk, butter, sugar, salt, lemon or vanilla flavor, cinnamon, and flour together, stir into mixture 5/6 marshmallows, raisins and pineapple.	Place batter in baking dish bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.
Remove
from oven and place marshmallow on top.
Cook for an additional 10 minutes.

title: double quick dinner rolls
directions: In bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Stir sugar, half of flour and salt into yeast.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in rest of flour until smooth.
Cover bowl with cloth.
Let rise about 30 minutes or longer in warm place.

title: baked spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions. Drain thoroughly, using hands to squeeze out excess liquid.
Heat oven to 350°.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients.
Stir to mix completely. Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes. Serve warm.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage with sugar until tender.
Drain well.
Add oleo. Combine
soup
and
cheese
in saucepan until cheese is melted. Mix
with
cabbage
and put into casserole dish.
Put crumbs
over top and dot with oleo.
Bake uncovered in 350° to 400° oven until bubbly.

title: my own sloppy joe mix
directions: Serve on hamburger buns, lightly toasted if you like.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper in oil in medium size heavy skillet until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add garlic; cook 1 minute.
Combine in ground turkey or beef.
Saute until half done, about 2 minutes. Add chili powder, cumin, oregano, basil, thyme, salt and pepper. Cook just until meat is cooked through, about 3 minutes.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes and 3/4 cup water.
Bring to boil, lower heat and simmer, stirring constantly, about 30 minutes. Spoon about 1/2 cup of filling until each buns is stuffed full. Serve hot.
Drain off excess grease of meat mixture.

title: company chicken and rice
directions: Spread rice in bottom of baking dish large enough to hold chicken pieces.
Arrange pieces of chicken on top of rice (may be touching but not overlapping).
Salt and pepper chicken to taste; sprinkle a thin layer of paprika over all.
Combine soup with enough water to make 2 cups.
Pour soup and water over chicken and rice.
Cover dish with aluminum foil; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a pie dish for 45 minutes at 350°.
Frozen spinach can be quickly thawed in microwave oven.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix well milk, sugar, coconut and nuts.
Roll into balls. Melt wax and chocolate chips slowly over low heat while stirring. Dip balls in chocolate mixture.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Combine the soup with the milk; heat. Serve over cooked vegetables or fish.

title: quick blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except blueberries and pecans.
Fold in pecans and blueberries.
Pour in greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hot cranberry salad
directions: Grease 2-quart sauce baking pan.
Place apples, cranberries, sugar and lemon juice in pan.
Cover with oatmeal mixture.
Pour on top of fruit.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt margarine. In a bowl, mix flour, sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stir in melted margarine.
In a bowl, slightly mash peaches and pour over the batter in the pan.
Bake until done.

title: sugar cured meat
directions: Mix spices well and spread on meat.
Sew in a square cloth and hang joint with bone end down to drain.
If joint weighs over 20 pounds double recipe.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients. Make into long rolls about 3 inches wide.
Chill overnight.
Next day, slice thin slices and put on greased cookie sheet.
Make a thin icing of water and powdered sugar.
Brush over each slice with pastry brush.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tender sirloin tip roast
directions: Sprinkle the roast with tenderizer as the label directs, then roast it in slow oven (300° to 325°) like standing rib roast.
It takes about 2 1/4 hours for a 4 pound sirloin tip to roast rare, 2 3/4 hours for well done meat.
If you use a roast-meat thermometer, the temperatures are 140° for rare, 160° for medium and 170° for well done.
Serve warm or cold.
If you wish to serve the roast cold in sandwiches, cook it a day ahead, cool and chill without slicing.
When ready to make sandwiches, slice the cold meat very thin and place it in large, buttered, crusty rolls.
The thinner you slice it, the tenderer the meat seems.
Makes enough for 8 generously filled sandwiches.

title: lillian's bread pudding
directions: Cube bread into a 9-inch square pan sprayed with Pam.
Beat sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla and cinnamon together.
Pour over bread cubes.
Stir in raisins.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in glass jar for months.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Mix the mashed bananas and 1/3 cup buttermilk together.
Add to first mixture; beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and the eggs; beat another 2 minutes.
Add chopped walnuts if desired.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Grease and flour pan.

title: swiss steak(serves 6)
directions: Mix flour, salt and paprika.
Cut steak in pieces.
Dredge in flour mix and fry in hot oil until golden.
Remove pieces as they brown to a Dutch oven.
When meat is all fried, stir remaining flour mix into the oil in pan.
Stir to blend.
Add tomatoes and stir.
If too thick, add beef consomme.
Sprinkle onions, celery and pepper over meat pieces in pan.
Add the bay leaf.
Add the Worcestershire sauce to the tomato mixture.
Pour over steak in pan.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° to 375° oven for 2 hours.

title: roast beef with horseradish sauce
directions: Boil beef, carrot, leek and salt in 1 1/2-quarts water until tender.
Remove beef and cut into thick sliess.
Place on serving dish and add the sauce to each slice.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil the cocoa, sugar, sweet milk and butter for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, salt and peanut butter.
Beat this in as quick as possible.
Then add oatmeal.
Drop on wax paper the size you desire.

title: potato casserole
directions: Line pan with foil.
Put layers of potatoes, onion, bacon bits, salt and pepper.
Slice 1 1/2 sticks of butter on the top layer and seal foil.
Cook 2 to 3 hours.
Fifteen minutes before potatoes are fully cooked, put cheese on top and reseal.
Finish cooking.
Do not peel potatoes.

title: pan cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Combine shortening, granulated	sugar,	brown sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat until creamy.
Add
eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.	Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until just tender (about 5 minutes). Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Add melted margarine to stuffing mix.
If stuffing is in cubes, crunch with rolling pin while still in the bag.
Place half of the stuffing on bottom of 8 x 10-inch pan.
Add cream mixture.
Top with remaining stuffing. Bake at 350° for about 20 or 30 minutes.

title: party nibbles(microwave)
directions: Mix cereal and nuts in a large bowl.
Melt butter on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in seasoning.
Drizzle over cereal.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until evenly toasted.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: chicken with creamed mushroom sauce
directions: Rinse off chicken.
Place in roasting pan.
Place pieces of cheese over chicken until all of chicken is covered.
Mix 1/2 cup of water with soup.
Pour over chicken.
Add sliced carrots and mushrooms.
Cover with foil.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
Serve over rice or egg noodles.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Boil wild rice, water and salt, then drain.
Brown ground meat. Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in butter.
Combine in bowl the soy sauce, sour cream, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix together with rice, meat and mushroom mixtures.
Add toasted almonds.
Bake in uncovered 3-quart casserole for about 1 hour at 375°.
Add water if necessary.
Stir casserole occasionally.
Can add water chestnuts, if desired.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: yogurt and cucumber salad dressing
directions: Peel cucumber. Cut in half and remove seeds. Grate enough cucumber to measure 1 cup.
Press cucumber between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Place yogurt in small bowl.
Mix in salt, garlic powder and dill weed. Drizzle oil over yogurt and mix well. Stir in cucumber. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Store, covered, in the refrigerator for up to 1 week.

title: marinated brisket of beef
directions: Mix all ingredients; place brisket in a covered pan.
Pour marinade over brisket.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Cook in oven in covered pan at 350° for about 3 hours or until tender. Slice brisket and serve with marinade sauce from pan.

title: mom's chicken
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, garlic powder, salt and pepper together.
Marinate chicken in sour cream mixture at least 2 hours or overnight.
Roll in crushed cornflakes.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.

title: mom's mega meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix the first 8 ingredients together.
The mixture should not be too wet.
If so, add some more bread crumbs so that the meat will hold a loaf shape.
Shape into a loaf in a large baking pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour; drain off drippings.

title: grandma's banana bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.	Beat shortening until creamy. Add sugar.	Gradually beat until light and fluffy.	Add eggs. Beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas.	Beat until smooth.
Bake in a greased bread pan for 1 hour at 325° to 350°. Check for doneness with knife in center.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter well.
Add eggs that have been beaten. Mix salt, 1 cup flour and baking powder together and sift over fruit and nuts.
Add dates mixed with 1/4 cup flour to other ingredients.
Combine all and bake in your largest pan.
Line pan with wax paper and cook for 3 hours at 300°.
Save the green and red cherries to decorate cake.
Use Karo syrup to hold cherries on cake.

title: mile-high biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar. Cut shortening into flour mixture with pastry blender.
Stir in sugar.
Mix together egg and milk; add to other ingredients and stir to form a sticky dough.
Turn onto floured surface and knead 6 to 8 times.
Roll or pat dough to 1/2-inch thick; cut out biscuits with floured cutter.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased sheet.
Makes about 15 biscuits.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in dry Jell-O; let set overnight.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nuts; set aside.
Melt oleo or shortening in saucepan (if shortening is used add 1 tablespoon hot water).
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Cool slightly.
Add egg and vanilla; blend.
Stir in flour mixture a little at a time mixing well after each addition.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool in pan and cut into bars.

title: deluxe nacho dip
directions: Brown sausage, ground meat and onion.
Drain fat.
In large pot melt cheese, salsa and cream of mushroom soup.
Mix all together and serve warm with tortilla chips.
Enjoy!

title: easy pecan bars
directions: Lightly grease a 13x9x2 baking pan; set aside. Set aside 1 c. of the cake mix for the filling. For crust, in large mixing bowl combine remaining cake mix, butter, and slightly beaten egg. Stir with a fork until crumbly. Turn into the prepared pan. With lightly floured hands, press evenly on the bottom to form a crust. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes. Meanwhile, for filling, in a medium mixing bowl combine the 3 eggs, brown sugar, corn syrup, and vanilla. Add the 1 c. reserved cale mix; stir with a fork just until blended. (Some tiny cake mix clumps will remain). Spread filling evenly over baked crust; sprinkle pecans atop. Bake for 25-30 minutes or until filling appears set when pan is gently shaken. Cool completely in the pan on a wire rack. Cut into bars. Cover and chill to store. Makes 48 bars.

title: potato yeast rolls
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and salt.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add mashed potatoes.
(You may mix up a cup of instant potatoes.) Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to mixture.
Work in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Place dough in a large covered container and place in refrigerator.
Dough will keep at least a week.
Just remove from refrigerator and make into rolls and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 400°.

title: greek roast lamb
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut slits in roast and insert half of the garlic slivers.
Combine remaining garlic, oil, lemon juice, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 2 teaspoons oregano in a small saucepan.
Heat and stir until well blended.
Brush lamb with the sauce.
Sprinkle remaining spices over the meat.
Roast 30 minutes per pound, basting with the oil mixture frequently. Let rest 10 minutes before carving.
Garnish platter with lemon slices and sprigs of mint.

title: lo-cal barbecue sauce(low sodium)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan; simmer slowly for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Refrigerate and use as needed.
"Excellent on chicken and fish," Kay says.

title: green pepper and italian sausage
directions: Brown sausage.
Add tomato sauce and about half of the water. Cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.
Add more water if too thick.
Serve on rolls.

title: gnocchi(italian dumplings)
directions: Beat eggs and Ricotta cheese.
Add flour to make a soft firm dough.
Roll small pieces of dough and shape over a cheese grater. Place thumb on dough and roll forward.
Place gnocchi in a large pan of boiling water.
Cook about 20 minutes or until tender. Serve with your favorite tomato-meat sauce and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Recipe may be doubled.
Gnocchi freezes well.

title: angela's french dressing
directions: Mix in bowl and beat with a rotary beater.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and beat.
Add bananas, milk and lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Add nuts. Bake in well-greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°. Makes 1 loaf.

title: sour cream twists(bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir all ingredients together.
Turn dough onto floured surface and fold several times to smooth. Roll dough into a 24 x 6-inch rectangle. Spread 1/2 dough (lengthwise) with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/3 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Fold other half over. Cut into strips 1-inch wide.
Hold strips at both ends and twist. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes. While warm, frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just tender.
Drain and place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in pan and stir in flour.
Cook together for a few minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and blend in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, and simmer until thickened.
Add pepper and salt. Pour over broccoli in casserole dish.
Combine stuffing, water and one half cup of butter.
Spoon on top of casserole, pressing down, if necessary.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Add cooked rice, cooked broccoli, celery, onions, Cheez Whiz and soup.
Put into baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Scald milk and to it, add the shortening, sugar, salt and lemon rind.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in beaten eggs and softened yeast.
Add 1/2 the flour and beat thoroughly.
Add remaining flour and mix well.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead lightly.
Place in greased bowl; cover and set in warm place.
Allow dough to rise until double in bulk.

title: overnight coleslaw
directions: Mix finely chopped onion with sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed until thoroughly mixed (in food processor if available). Gradually add pimiento and chop in processor 4 or 5 times (lightly) or chop by hand and add to mixture.
Pour mixture over cabbage, stir until evenly coated.
Allow to marinade, cover, in refrigerator 8 hours.
Stir slaw and drain off excess liquid.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients and fold in.
Spread on jellyroll pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out onto towel.
Spread with filling. Roll and allow to stand for 1 hour before serving.

title: eggplant-corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Peel eggplant.
Dice. Cook eggplant in boiling water until tender. Drain and mash.
Combine onion, eggplant, corn, soup and seasoning in greased casserole. Cover with crumbs. Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sweet, saucy meatballs
directions: Combine ground chuck, cracker crumbs, chili sauce, onion, eggs, salt and pepper; mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls and place in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over meatballs. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover last 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Salt chicken and boil until tender.
Cool; remove from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken broth, soup and cream cheese together.
Melt butter and pour over cracker crumbs.
Layer crackers in bottom of a baking dish, then the soup mixture. Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth for 1 minute in blender or on high for 2 minutes with electric beaters.
Pour into pie plate and bake for 50 to 55 minutes until knife comes out clean.

title: white chili
directions: Combine beans, chicken broth, garlic and half of the onions in a large soup pot and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until beans are very soft, 3 hours or more.
Add more chicken broth, if needed.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows; stir until dissolved.
Soften cream cheese (can use soft variety) with juice of pineapple.
Add to jello mixture.
Add pineapple, mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Put into 1 large mold or individual ones. This may be used as salad or dessert.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Beat together flour, sugar, milk and margarine.
Pour over fruit in a square pan, about 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab muffins
directions: Melt oleo and add to cheese, mayo, salt and crab.
Mix together.
Lightly toast muffin halves and then spread mixture on each.
Cook at 375° for 12 to 20 minutes, depending on whether frozen or not.
Cut in fourths and serve hot.
May be fixed ahead and frozen.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes and salt.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°, then bake 40 minutes.
This will make 1 pie.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: play dough
directions: Combine ingredients in a pot.
Stir until thick.
Form into a ball and store in a covered container in your refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If too dry, add more tomatoes and juice, depending on how much hamburger you have.
For 6 people families, I use 4 pounds of hamburger and double ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 1/2 hours for larger meat loaf.

title: corn cheese pie
directions: Rub butter over bottom and sides of pie shell.
Saute onion in small amount of bacon drippings.
Reserve 5 to 6 slices of bacon for garnish and crumble rest into onion.
Spread over bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle cup of cheese over this.
Set aside.
Heat milk, add eggs, corn and rest of cheese until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in hot oven, 450° for ten minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° for 25 minutes more.

title: onion sauteed chicken
directions: Take a package of chicken thighs and remove skin.
Make 1 slice into the meat on top side of chicken.
Soak chicken in vinegar. Can be soaked all day or 1 hour prior to cooking.
Slice onions and place on top of chicken.
Take frying pan and place chicken, vinegar and onions in pan.
Add water, enough to cover top of chicken.
Boil slowly until chicken is done.
Gives chicken a tangy taste.
Serve with anything.

title: vegetable salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together, serve with chips of choice. Store in refrigerator, covered.

title: cheese ring with strawberry preserves
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup pecans in an oiled ring mold and press cheese mixture into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: grape juice crush
directions: Mix all ingredients except for ginger ale.
Chill well.
Just before serving, slowly pour in ginger ale.
Serve over crushed ice.
Enjoy this on a hot summer day!!

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix well; roll out and fill with stewed fruits.
Fry in deep oil.

title: garlic slaw
directions: Pour over approximately 2 cups shredded cabbage.
Can add carrots and/or bell pepper if desired.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight in enough cold water to cover beans. Drain.
Add 2 quarts of water, ham bone, onions, carrots, celery, parsley, cloves, mace, thyme, bay leaves, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat, and simmer gently for 2 to 3 hours or until beans are very tender. Remove ham and bone, cutting any meat into small pieces.
Work soup through a sieve or blend in an electric blender.
Add diced ham and sherry and season to taste.
If soup is too thick (it should look like heavy cream), stir in a little water.
Reheat and serve with sliced hard-cooked eggs and thin lemon slices on top. Serves 6.

title: hot spaghetti dish
directions: Place spaghetti in boiling water (salted).
Boil until soft. When done, put in colander and rinse.
Fry meat.
Add chopped celery and onions and cook until soft.
Put altogether with other ingredients into small roaster or large baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Use 1/2 recipe for smaller families.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk, sugar, salt and butter until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until thick, pour into a 9 x 9 pan spray with a cooking spray.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Crush crackers and spread in oblong pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and pour on butter.
Mix or mash with spoon or fork to make crust. Mix cream cheese and icing together; pour on crust.
Add sliced strawberries and glaze.

title: marzipan candy
directions: Grind almonds very fine and combine with powdered sugar until well blended.
Make a well in center of mixture and add unbeaten egg whites.
Knead to a smooth consistency that does not stick when working with a spatula, then by hand.
If it is too dry, add more egg whites.
Paste should be moist enough to be formed into any desired shape.
Keep paste covered while shaping, as it dries out easily.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Season pork chops; coat with flour.
Brown in hot fat in frying pan.
Place potatoes in saucepan with water and 1/2 teaspoon salt; cover.
Heat to boiling; cook 5 to 8 minutes. Drain thoroughly.
Place potatoes and onion in buttered 12 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Mix celery soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Arrange browned pork chops on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender and pork chops are well done, about 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Shake well before each using.

title: whipped frosting
directions: Put cornstarch and milk in pan; bring to boil, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick.
Set aside to cool.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add cooled mixture; beat together.
Add vanilla and beat until frosting is the consistency of whipped cream.
Frosting for Crazy Chocolate Cake.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Brown chops in large skillet and pour off drippings.
Stir in soup, water, potatoes, carrots, Worcestershire sauce, salt and caraway seed.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until chops are tender.

title: soft top rolls
directions: Mix yeast in milk.
Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl. Rub the surface with vegetable oil.
Leave in warm place until double in bulk, about 3 hours.
Form into rolls the size of pullet eggs.
Place in large greased muffin pans.
Let rise until double. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cool broccoli; drain.
Melt 1/2 stick butter and Velveeta. Toss the well drained broccoli into the cheese mix.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Top with Ritz cracker topping.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes (do not peel). Slice 1/2 inch thick.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dip slices in milk then in flour.
Dip in beaten egg, then in dry bread crumbs.
Fry in 10 inch skillet in hot oil over medium heat.
Cook about 4 minutes, brown on each side turning once.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes. Fill jars.
Seal.
Process 30 minutes in hot water bath.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening, margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend well with shortening mixture. Combine sugar and cinnamon in small bowl.
Form dough into 1-inch balls and roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: trifle
directions: Crumble cake in bottom of pan. Boil 1 cup of water and mix in jello.
Add frozen strawberries. Stir until mixture begins to jell. Pour 1/2 over cake.
Pour vanilla pudding that has been mixed with milk over jello.
Put in refrigerator and let set. Top with Cool Whip.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix flour and
baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating well.
Add vanilla.
Divide batter into 2 parts.
Add nuts to one part.
Bake in 3 layers. Add nutmeg, raisins and cinnamon to the other batter.
Bake in 3 layers.
Bake at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix last 3 ingredients for topping and spread over loaf when about half baked so topping doesn't get too dark.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put in cherry filling and pineapple. Stir.
Then spread evenly. Add dry cake mix and top with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Spread popped corn and peanuts in a large shallow sheet pan. Keep warm in 250° oven.
Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt in a heavy pan. Place on medium heat.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda (syrup will form).
Pour syrup over popped corn and peanuts in a fine stream.
Stir and mix well.
Return to oven and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and serve or store in an airtight container.
Keep in a cool place, but very good served warm.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order given in a crock-pot. Fill the crock-pot with water, covering all of the ingredients. Cook 10 hours on high.
May add a dash of Texas Pete, if desired. Also, may serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine scrubbed and diced potatoes, onion, celery and parsley in pot.
Cover with water and cook until potatoes are done. Remove from heat.
Add milk, crisp precooked bacon and butter. Return to heat for a few minutes.
Do not boil.
Remove.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: basic french dressing
directions: Shake well and chill.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
After mashing the potatoes, add the cream cheese, sour cream, butter, salt and pepper.
Whip or beat with electric beaters.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add potatoes; dot with butter.
Sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Cook beef and onion until browned and onion is soft. Drain off fat and stir in ketchup and chili powder. Add water and let simmer for 10 minutes.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar, oil, eggs and beans beating until smooth.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder and soda together. Add to bean mixture stirring until just combined.
Stir in raisins and vanilla; fill 5 greased and floured 16 ounce cans 2/3 full.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely before serving.
May be baked in one 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients and make into balls.
Place in a baking pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes, onion and asparagus spears.
Place in pan. Cover with enough water to cook done.
Add butter, milk, salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat about 5 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger or sausage in a pan.
Put both cheeses, picante sauce, chilies and meat in crock-pot; let melt.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: curry chutney cheese ball
directions: Mix curry well into softened cream cheese.
Form into ball and refrigerate.
Cut big pieces in the curry in half.
When ready to serve, place cheese ball on plate.
Pour chutney over it.
Ball may be rolled in finely ground almonds, if desired, or sprinkle slivered almonds on top.

title: one dish meal
directions: Wash potatoes.
With skin on, cut in half lengthwise.
Dice onion and peel and slice carrots.
Layer potatoes and onion in a large electric skillet.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes, then add rest of vegetables and cover.
Cook until potatoes are tender. Fry cutlets and cook gravy.
Put cutlets on top of vegetables and pour gravy over top.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt first three ingredients on Low in microwave.
Add peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni or other pasta al dente.
Brown hamburger with onions and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and heat.
Serve with a mixed salad.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix
in
large bowl.
Freeze and remove from freezer 20 minutes before serving.
