title: first pizza pie
directions: Pat dough into tiara pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes, or until done.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together. When cake is cooled, turn onto plate and pour cheese and sugar mixture in middle of cake.
Arrange fruit on top.
Good with strawberries, fresh peaches or Mandarin oranges.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Coarsely crumble cornbread, then add tomato, onion, cucumber and bacon bits.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten, then add Italian salad dressing to taste.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer in order in serving bowl.
Serve chilled.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and then add the remaining ingredients.
Spray the pan with Pam. Bake at 350° until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: dipped chocolates
directions: Blend margarine and powdered sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into balls (with #100 scoop) and chill.

title: cabbage and carrot casserole
directions: Cook cabbage, carrots and onion 20 minutes and drain.
Put in a greased casserole.
Make a white sauce of the milk, butter and salt and then add the cheese.
When cheese is melted, pour over vegetables.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake in a moderate oven for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine and spread.
If not thin enough to spread, add mayonnaise.

title: pineapple-poached carrots
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until carrots are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: drop oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: corn balls
directions: In saucepan, cook onion and celery in butter until tender; set aside to cool.
In bowl, combine croutons, corn, eggs, water, salt, pepper and onion mixture; mix well.
Shape into 8 to 10 balls.
Place in an ungreased shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 corn balls.

title: chocolate cream dessert
directions: Cut margarine into flour.
Add nuts.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 325° (glass pan) or at 350° in a metal pan.
Mix 8 ounces softened cream cheese with 1 cup powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Carefully spread on top of cooled crust.

title: mystery meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chili sauce, together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Place strips of bell pepper on top halfway through cooking.
Pour off fat halfway through cooking. Cook until meat shrinks from sides of pan.

title: stromboli
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Combine parsley, pepper, oil, oregano, garlic powder, Parmesan cheese and egg yolks and spread on rolled out bread dough.
Layer 1/2 pound pepperoni (sliced) and 12 ounces Provolone cheese (sliced) on top of mixture.
Roll dough like a jelly roll, and place on greased cookie sheet.
Be sure to place rolled stromboli, seam down.
Brush top of roll with egg whites. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: wiener bites
directions: Mix ingredients; melt in saucepan.
When blended and bubbly, add wieners, cut into bite size pieces.

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Remove filling from Oreos and crush cookies.
Mix with melted margarine and press onto bottom of 10-inch pie pan or spring-form. Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Blend flour into egg mixture and shape dough into 1-inch balls. Roll balls into a sugar and cinnamon mixture until coated.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Let cool for 1 minute before removing from pan.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat egg until light yellow, fluffy and thick.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in pancake mix and nuts.
Drop on greased and floured cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add spinach after being squeezed as dry as possible.
Add rest of ingredients; roll into 2-inch balls. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli tuna roll-ups
directions: Combine soup and milk; set aside. Combine tuna, broccoli, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions. Stir in 3/4 cup soup mixture. Divide tuna mixture evenly between the tortillas and roll up. Place seam-side down in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour remaining soup over the top. Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes. Top center with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: orange date bread
directions: Place the orange juice in a small saucepan and bring to a boil over high heat.
Place the dates in a small bowl and pour the orange juice over the dates.
Set and cool.

title: 7 layer salad(make day before)
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch glass dish, layer ingredients in following order: head of lettuce (chopped), celery, onion, peanuts, Parmesan cheese and frozen peas.
Spread on layer of mayonnaise. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with chopped bacon, tomatoes and eggs before serving.

title: anise cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, blend sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla and anise.
Add flour, baking powder and soda mixture alternately with milk. Shape into long narrow rolls on a greased sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Slice while hot into 3/4-inch slices, then toast under broiler until brown on both sides.

title: deer camp sausage casserole
directions: Tear bread in pieces and place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Spread sausage over bread and sprinkle with cheese. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Add mushrooms. Pour over bread and sausage. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: old-fashioned shortbread cookies
directions: Mix margarine and lard well.
Add sugar.
Mix. Add flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each.
Mold dough in logs.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill for 24 hours or more.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until solid, not brown.

title: kelly's egg rolls
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain.
Boil water, adding vermicelli. Cook until tender; don't overcook.
Drain.
Cut vermicelli into short pieces.
Wash bean sprouts and break into very small pieces.
Chop cabbage, onions, peppers and carrots very finely.

title: ribs in a pot
directions: Parboil ribs.
Place in heavy Dutch oven.
Cover with sliced onions.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a small pan; bring to boil.
Pour over ribs.
Cover.
Cook on low 2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: chocolate chews
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla together.
Beat eggs and add to mixture, then add melted chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients together, adding alternately with first mixture and milk.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in nuts (if using).
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Form balls, 1-inch in diameter.
Roll in powdered sugar and place on greased baking sheet, 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except beans.
Mix well.
Then add beans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12 baking pan.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk and pour on top of butter.
Add fruit on top of that (do not drain fruit). Do not stir.
Bake at 400 degrees for at least 30-45 minutes.
Is very good with vanilla ice cream.

title: the best sandwich in the world
directions: Place 1 piece of bread on your left and the other piece on your right. Spread a generous amount of peanut butter on the left piece, being sure to cover the bread completely. Spread grape jelly on the right piece, also being sure to cover the bread completely (Spun honey may be used as a substitute for jelly). Take the left piece and place directly on top of the right piece, being sure that the crusts line up exactly. Press together lightly, just until the peanut butter begins to ooze out. Best eaten with glass of milk.

title: pasta with vodka *
directions: Saute red pepper flakes in butter for about 1 minute.
Add vodka and bring to boil.
Lower heat; add tomatoes and simmer ten minutes.
Add cream and basil and simmer briefly.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in butter.
Drain water chestnuts, saving liquid to dilute soup.
Remove sauteed vegetables from skillet and combine with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs over and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 generously.

title: broccoli italian style(makes 4 servings, 2-cup measure)
directions: Combine butter and onions in 2-cup measure.
Microwave 2 minutes on High or until onions are transparent.
Stir in pimiento, lemon juice, salt, pepper and oregano.
Pour over cooked and drained broccoli.
Microwave 4 minutes on High or until hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir into zucchini mixture until well mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into two well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: pollo alla angelo(chicken angelo-milan)
directions: Thoroughly wash and dry chicken pieces.
Dip each piece in egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet and brown chicken on both sides.
Transfer chicken to baking dish.
Add chicken stock and bay leaf.
Cover and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Place a piece of cheese on each piece of chicken.
Cover and return to oven for 7 to 8 minutes.
Serve with boiled potatoes, rice or pasta alfredo.

title: finnish nisu
directions: Scald milk; add margarine, 3/4 cup sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar to warm water.
Allow to set for 5 minutes or until foamy.
Beat eggs; add eggs and lukewarm milk mixture to yeast.
Blend well. Add 2 cups flour and ground cardamon; beat well.
Gradually add remaining flour until dough is easy to handle.
Knead on a floured surface until smooth and satiny.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise free from draft until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Beat margarine with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add 1/4 cup of the sugar. Beat until combined.
Beat in the one cup flour until crumbly.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream butter and stir in sour cream, lemon and vanilla.
With a fork, blend together flour, sugar and baking soda. Add to butter mixture.
Fold in the egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in greased Bundt pan.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: easy seafood dip
directions: If large pieces, cut into smaller size or be sure other shellfish is free of cartilage.
Add all ingredients and mix well. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind vegetables, using coarse blade.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetable mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes. Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Yields 8 pints.

title: lobster - like fish
directions: Combine.
Bring to a boil.
Let steep for 1/2 hour. Bring back to a boil.
Add fish.
Cook until white (1 to 2 minutes). Serve with lemon and melted margarine.

title: barbecue sauce for spareribs
directions: Combine ingredients; cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Pour over ribs that have been browned.
Pork spareribs or beef short ribs both are good.
Bake slowly for 2 hours or until done at 325°.

title: good pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix good.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: franks with pork and beans
directions: Slice franks lengthwise, almost through. In frying pan, cook onions in butter until tender. Add franks. Brown slowly on all sides. Add pork and beans, sugar and catsup.
Cook slowly 20 minutes. Serve on toasted frankfurter buns.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable rice casserole
directions: Fry onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add undiluted soup and simmer.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Meanwhile, cook broccoli and drain, and cook rice and drain.

title: party meat balls
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and stir well.
Roll out in walnut size balls and lay in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix well and make sure cranberry sauce is mashed well.
Pour over meat balls and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and warm water.
Add to mix sugar, oil and cake mix.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Add melted oleo. Mix until smooth.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: creamy macaroni salad
directions: Set mixture aside and add to the following:

title: spanish style "flan" custard
directions: In a small pot, melt the sugar to a caramel point.
When done, put it in a mold.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in large bowl.
Quarter biscuits, separate and drop into sugar mixture, keeping quarters separate. Shake sugar mixture to coat.
Drop pieces into Bundt pan loosely. Melt butter and pour into remaining sugar mixture and stir.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn bread out of pan onto a plate while hot.

title: sugarless fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler over hot water.
When melted, add Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Stir quickly!!! Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: swedish ham balls
directions: Combine in small bowl the first 4 ingredients until completely dissolved.
This is the sauce that goes over the ham balls.
Make balls and arrange in baking dish; pour sauce over all.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Baste frequently with sauce. Yields about 45 sweet and sour nuggets.

title: zucchini with potatoes
directions: In skillet, cook onion in oil until tender, but not brown. Stir in vegetables, oregano, salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Cook, covered, until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Combine 1 cup boiling water and candy.
Mix until completely dissolved. Add gelatin. Stir to dissolve.
Blend in applesauce. Pour half the mixture into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Chill until firm. Blend remaining ingredients together.
Pour over firm applesauce mixture.
Pour remaining applesauce over cream cheese mixture. Chill until firm.

title: baked buttermilk chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish, combine all ingredients, except chicken, until blended.
Add chicken and turn each piece several times to coat.
Bake, turning twice, until cooked through, about 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot percolator punch
directions: Pour first 3 ingredients into a
12-cup percolator.
Place remaining ingredients, except whole cinnamon sticks, in percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle of electric percolator.
Serve with cinnamon stick stirrers, if desired.
Yields about 7 cups.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix oil, juice and eggs.
Add cake mix.
Beat 3 minutes.
Put into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place oranges evenly over top before baking.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Combine all ingredients as listed; mix well.
Pour into a greased baking pan (Bundt or angel food pan).
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, ice with your favorite icing.

title: italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and margarine. Gradually add the confectioners sugar and vanilla. Stir in nuts.

title: no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine
peanut butter, sugar and butter in mixing bowl and beat well.
Stir in cereal and mix well.
Shape into balls and flatten
with
fork.
Place
these
on
wax
paper.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip cookies in chocolate and place back on waxed paper to cool.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Mix well sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour with coconut, corn flakes, soda, salt and baking powder. Bake until light at 350°.

title: bird nest cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla and egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir in flour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip into slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in nuts or coconut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, one inch apart.
Make a depression in center of cookie.
Place chocolate bits in center of cookie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Date nut filling or jam can be used instead of chocolate bits.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onions in butter. Add ground beef, garlic, flour, salt, m.s.g., pepper and paprika. Saute 5 minutes. Add mushrooms, cream of chicken or mushroom soup and tomato sauce; simmer 5 minutes. Add sour cream to taste when ready to serve. Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on baking sheet. Flatten with folk.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage corn chowder
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook sausage until brown.
Spoon off fat.
Add onions and cook 1 minute, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup, milk, corn, cheese and hot pepper sauce, stirring occasionally, until hot.

title: baked fish
directions: Prepare a shallow baking dish with nonstick cooking spray or oil, butter or shortening.
Combine Miracle Whip, mustard, onion, parsley and soy sauce in bowl.
Dip each piece of fish in the mixture, then arrange in a single layer in the prepared pan. Sprinkle the bread crumbs on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°. Test for doneness by cutting into the thickest piece.

title: pink lavender lemonade
directions: In a saucepan, combine 2 1/2 cups water with sugar and the Hibiscus flowers.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve the sugar.
Simmer for a few minutes to extract the color of the Hibiscus.
Then remove from the heat.
Stir in the lavender leaves and allow mixture to cool with lid on.

title: chicken dorito casserole
directions: Layer 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with Doritos, then one layer of chicken.
Heat soup and pour over chicken.
Top with mushrooms. Put raw onion rings over this.
Cover with cheese slices.
Bake at 300° until bubbly.

title: cabbage pudding("kal pudding")
directions: Heat oven to 390°F/200°C.
Mince the cabbage head (except the coarse parts).
Parboil in salted water; pour off water.
Mince the onion and mash the potatoes.
Mix all ingredients for the filling, except bread crumbs and butter.
Flavor with salt and pepper.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables and drain.
Mix vegetables, onions, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Put in a greased casserole dish. Cover with 1 package of crushed Ritz crackers mixed with 1 stick butter or margarine (melted).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: sunday steaks and potatoes
directions: Line a large, heavy baking pan with foil.
Place potatoes and carrots on foil.
Salt and pepper.
Add round steak.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle with garlic.
Salt and pepper.
Wrap tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for about 2 hours.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all and chill overnight.
Serves 6.

title: sweet and sour sausage balls
directions: Shape sausage in small balls.
Fry at medium heat until golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.
Pour off grease.
Return sausage to skillet.
Add catsup, brown sugar, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add drained pineapple chunks.
Place in chafing dish.
Serve hot. Yields 5 dozen.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Water should be warm enough you cannot keep your hand under it but no hotter.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all other ingredients together, then add dissolved yeast.
Place towel over mixture; let stand 30 minutes.
Roll out and cut into circles. Spread melted butter (squeeze butter will be fine) on top and then fold half into.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ham delights
directions: Slice rolls completely through middle, separating top from bottom.
(If you place rolls in freezer for a while, it makes cutting easy.)
Cream margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion.
Spread on tops and bottoms of rolls.
Then add boiled ham and cheese, divided evenly over rolls.
Wrap in foil. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
To serve, cut into individual rolls.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add beans and taco seasoning.
Let cool.
Combine lettuce, tomatoes, onions, black olives and cheese. Mix in small amount of dressing.
Add meat mixture.
Crumble Doritos in right before serving.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour and butter until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and powdered sugar together.
Spread on top of crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts if desired.

title: cauliflower 'n cheese
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender; drain.
Place in greased casserole.
In bowl, combine cheeses, crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle mixture over cauliflower.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix everything together and boil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Save broth.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour mixed broth, soup and vegetables over chicken.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Pour sliced peaches and juice into medium size
oblong baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inches is too large for
this
recipe).
Sprinkle
cinnamon generously over peaches. Top
with dry smooth cake mix.
Place pats of butter on top
of cake mix until completely covered.	Sprinkle cinnamon over butter. Bake at 350° until golden brown and bubbly.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Heat milk until almost hot.
Beat together the eggs and sugar until frothy.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add to heated milk slowly, stirring constantly while adding.
Bring to a roaring boil; turn off.
Pour into ice cream freezer until 2/3 full.
Cover and put into ice cream container.
Turn on freezer; add ice and rock salt and keep adding as needed.
Ice cream is finished when it rises to the top of freezer, about 45 minutes.
Keep in refrigerator.
If it becomes too firm, soften in microwave a few seconds to desired softness.

title: wild rice
directions: Fix rice as directed on box.
Add mushrooms and green onions to browned and drained sausage.
Add seasonings.
Add rice.
Can be put in crock-pot for serving later.

title: favorite casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: In a medium-size bowl, blend together butter, brown sugar and flour with a fork until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Put 1 cup of the mixture aside for topping.
Press remaining mixture into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Combine sugar and cream cheese, mixing until smooth.
Thoroughly beat in egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Spread over the baked crust and sprinkle with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool for at least 1 hour before cutting.

title: secret toffee
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Line the inside of a 13 x 19-inch pan with a good-sized sheet of foil, going about 1-inch up the sides. Melt the butter in a small saucepan; add the brown sugar and boil rapidly until sugar melts and becomes syrupy, about 30 seconds. Pour into the foil-lined pan.
Tilt pan to cover the bottom evenly.
Arrange a layer of the crackers, allowing about 1/8-inch between each.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate morsels and nuts over top.
Return to oven 1 minute more.
Remove and spread chocolate evenly over sugar and crackers with spatula.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or more, until firm.
Lift from pan. Peel off foil and break into chunks.
Refrigerate for storage.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Mix dry
ingredients.
Reserve half of noodles for top. Pour liquids
over dry ingredients.
Put in greased casserole; top with noodles. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt
chips with milk.	In a large bowl, combine 2 cups dry roasted
peanuts and 1 (10 1/2 ounce bag) miniature marshmallows. Pour
chocolate
mixture into nut mixture; mix well. Spread on wax paper.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese and Hidden Valley dressing mix.
Spread cream cheese mixture on each tortilla.
Sprinkle each with green onions, green peppers, red peppers and black olives.
Press down into cream cheese.
Roll each tortilla up tightly.
Wrap each roll in plastic wrap and chill 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch slices before serving.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: mama's chicken-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine with all other ingredients and desired amount of mayonnaise.
This salad is best made a day ahead so all the flavors can blend together.

title: granny smith's red cabbage
directions: In large skillet, stir together all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until cabbage is tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook celery and sausage.
Add remaining items except peppers. Cook at least 20 minutes.
Add peppers and cook 10 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese on top and serve with hot bread.
Good with crackers, too.
You can add onion, carrots, anything else you like.
Delish!

title: cookie crumble
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring 3 minutes. Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin; mix well.
Blend in whipped topping until smooth.
Chill 15 minutes, until mixture will mound.
Crumble 1/2 of a cookie into each of 8 to 10 dessert glasses.
Fill 1/2 full with gelatin. Top with another 1/2 cookie, then fill glasses with gelatin. Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Shape into oblong patties. Brown in skillet.
Add the brown gravy mix and water.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Then add liquids.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cool whip fruit dip
directions: *If serving with fruit, omit pineapple.

title: thelma's cheese ball
directions: Chop beef and onion very fine.
Mix with all other ingredients and shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Beat until smooth.
Dough will be very soft.
Cover with damp cloth.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Shape as desired.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms.
Blend butter, parsley, onion, mustard, salt, cayenne, nutmeg and flour.
Lay mushrooms in casserole.
Pour cream over all.
Bake in uncovered dish for 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: quick cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
In a small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and whisk thoroughly. Pour into prepared pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: the best rice pudding
directions: Combine water, rice and salt in 1-quart pan. Boil for 7 minutes. Add milk and butter. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and cook for 1 1/4 hours.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla. Add to rice. Remove from heat.
Can add 1/2 cup raisins, if desired. Turn into buttered shallow pan and sprinkle with cinnamon/nutmeg sugar.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Arrange potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and parsley evenly in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients and spread evenly over potatoes.
Decorate top with more ketchup. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Mix instant vanilla pudding mix according to directions on box.
Add Eagle Brand milk; add Cool Whip.
Fold in.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pan and sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs with garlic;
drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients;
boil	until tender.
When tender, add cornstarch to thicken sauce.
Add pineapple (this is optional).

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Arrange in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Arrange chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over this, then sprinkle combined bread crumbs and melted butter over all.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Press onto bottom and 1-inch up sides of 9-inch spring-form pan or onto bottom only of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: cuban black beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to low heat; simmer 3 hours.
When beans are tender, add rice and serve.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: mountain high cake
directions: Mix ingredients and pour batter into 3 layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Place tamales in casserole dish. Mix chicken ala king and Ro-Tel tomatoes together. Pour over tamales. Add grated cheese to cover top. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and hot throughout, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange cookies with orange icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, sour cream and orange flavoring.
Sift together flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add alternately with orange juice to mixture until batter is stiff but not too dry or too soupy.
Add pecans, if desired.
Refrigerate for 1 hour but not longer than overnight. Place on buttered cookie sheet by rounded teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Bottoms should be only lightly browned.
Cool on wax paper-covered racks until ready to frost.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Mix refried beans and picante sauce and spread on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
for 2nd layer, blend avocados, mayonnaise and lemon juice in blender until smooth.
Spread on top of 1st layer.
For 3rd layer, blend sour cream and taco seasoning mix and spread on top of 2nd layer.
Top with Cheddar cheese, chopped tomatoes, black olives and green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large pot, saute onion in butter for 3 minutes. Add water and bouillon. Bring to a boil. Add noodles and pepper.
Cook 3 minutes. Stir in broccoli and garlic powder.
Cook 4 minutes. Add milk and cubed cheese slowly until melted and creamy, stirring constantly.
Keep on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sauce for fruit
directions: Blend
well in blender.
Pour over fruit (strawberries, grapes, bananas, etc.).

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn bread mix, add it last. Bake in greased 9 x 13 inch pan at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: black walnut chiffon cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl and then add oil, water, yolks and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Add walnuts.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Fold egg whites into first mixture.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake cake 1 hour or until done.

title: toffee bars
directions: Mix well.
Pat into 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
While this is baking, chop or grate one large Hershey or Nestle bar.
Spread over hot baked dough (working fast).
Sprinkle with ground nuts.
Pat nuts into chocolate with waxed paper.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: strawberries with amaretto sauce
directions: Mix together in blender until smooth.
Strawberries can be served with powdered sugar in a goblet with Amaretto sauce poured over the berries.
Extra Amaretto may be poured over berries before adding sauce.
Berries may be used plain and the sauce used as a dip.

title: egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Crumble over layer of crescent rolls. Add eggs and desired amount of Cheddar cheese.
Add another layer of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring well (dough will be sticky). Dust hands with powdered sugar and shape dough into 3/4-inch balls. Coat balls with powdered sugar and place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done. Remove cookies to wire racks to cool. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: quick and easy peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Rub butter on bottom and sides of a 2-quart casserole dish. Place sliced peaches in dish (save the juice). Mix juice from peaches, vanilla and 1/2 box of cake mix together. Stir real well. Pour over peaches. Dot remaining butter on top of mixture. Place dish in preheated oven and cook 25 to 30 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream of Cool Whip, if desired.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Cool and stir in milk.
Great for topping pound cake or ice cream.

title: coconut fruit bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Add more coconut if you really like the stuff.

title: springfield potato dish
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice each potato into 3 slices; cut potatoes across twice.
Fry over medium heat in oil, turning slowly.
Add bell peppers, onion, and garlic.
Cook potatoes until you can put a fork through them.
Drain oil from potatoes, sprinkle on salt, add water and stir, mixing well.
Place lid over pan and simmer until water has almost evaporated.
Serve with ketchup.
Good for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, pepper and peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream and
spread evenly.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon on sour cream mixture.
Then
sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Let stand for 12 hours.

title: dried lima beans
directions: Wash beans first, soak overnight in enough water to cover.
Put in a large pot.
Add white bacon, cut up potatoes and quarter onion.
Add a dash of garlic salt.
Cook until done.
Salt and pepper to taste as bacon may be enough.

title: italian lentil soup
directions: Place lentils, ham bone, onion and water in large stockpot and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Turn off heat, cover pot and soak 1 hour.
Bring to a second boil and simmer for 1 hour or until lentils are tender.
Remove ham bone and cut off chunks of meat , toss into pot and discard the bone.
Chop garlic and parsley together and add with tomato puree, olive oil and oregano to the pot.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: cooked finger paint
directions: Mix cornstarch and cold water together to form a smooth paste. Add boiling water, stirring vigorously.
Cook over low heat until paste is glossy, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
While mixture is still warm, add soap flakes.
Beat this mixture.
Add glycerine and pour into a jar.
Add powdered paint or vegetable coloring.

title: peanut butter munchies
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar, peanut butter and butter in a medium size mixing bowl.
Roll between palms to shape into balls (small). Roll half in nuts and half in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: zesty rice lasagna
directions: In large bowl, combine cooked rice, 1 egg and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
In another bowl, combine 1 egg, Mozzarella, Ricotta or cottage cheese, 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and parsley.
In large skillet, brown hamburger, breaking up.
Drain.
Add sauce and oregano.
Heat.
Evenly spread half of rice mixture into greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with half of cheese mixture and meat mixture.
Repeat all layers.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix well and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: frosted apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all pastry ingredients together.
Turn half of dough onto floured surface.
Roll into a 10 x 12 rectangle. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Add filling.
Roll out remaining dough and place over filling.
Fold edges together and crimp with fork.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Bake 40 minutes until golden.

title: monster cookies
directions: In dishpan, combine ingredients in the order listed, adding one at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Use an ice cream scoop and place mounds on a greased cookie sheet; flatten slightly. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 80 large cookies. Drop by teaspoon to make approximately 40 dozen cookies.

title: punch
directions: Freeze an ice ring at least 1 day in advance.
Place slices of fruit in jello mold and cover with water.
Pour the thawed concentrates in a large punch bowl.
Add 7-Up and ice ring.
Top with scoops of sherbet.

title: asparagus roll appetizer
directions: Cream the cheeses.
Cut crust off bread. Roll out bread, flattening with a rolling pin.
Spread cheese on bread.
Place one asparagus spear on the bread and roll it as for a jelly roll. Next, roll in melted butter and freeze.
Cut each log into 3 or 4 sections. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: basic ice cream(yields 2 quarts)
directions: Mix custard powder with a little cold milk.
Add to evaporated milk with slightly beaten eggs.
Cook over boiling water in a double boiler until mixture coats spoon.
Add 1 teaspoon gelatin dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water while the custard is hot.
Remove from heat; cool and add condensed milk or sugar if necessary. Flavor with vanilla or mixed essence.
Chill and freeze or churn in freezer.
Excellent served with either fruit cocktail, flaked coconut, peaches, pears or chocolate sauce.

title: spiders
directions: Melt the butterscotch chips over hot, not boiling water, in a double boiler.
Mix in the peanut butter.
Stir in the chow mein noodles.
Mix to coat well.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until set, about 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream the peanut butter with the oleo. Add the brown sugar. Cream together.
In a separate bowl, mix the flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with the eggs (one at a time), vanilla and milk. Bake in glass dish at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool and frost with Caramel Icing.

title: cher's quick pizza appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Split each pita loaf into 2 rounds. Toast lightly in oven.
Spray a nonstick cooking sheet with Pam. Place the 4 pita rounds on cookie sheet.
Spread each with 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce, 1/2 tablespoon onion and 1 tablespoon cheese. Bake for 4 to 6 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Cut each round into quarters and serve immediately.

title: sauteed vegetable medley
directions: Coat a large skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add garlic and onion; cook until onion is transparent, stirring constantly.
Add green pepper; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add yellow squash and zucchini; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, basil and pepper; cover and cook about 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 servings (about 55 calories per serving).

title: deer meat(crock-pot dish)
directions: Put in crock-pot in morning with 1/4 cup of water on low temperature.
Sprinkle soup mix on top of meat.
Drape bacon over meat.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook in crock-pot 9 to 10 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Stir all together and place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hungarian horns
directions: Mix flour, oleo, 3 egg yolks and water.
Put in refrigerator. When dough is cold, roll out in small balls, like little pies. Put jelly in it and roll; shape like horns.
Brush egg and milk mixture over horns or rolled up dough.
Next, sprinkle pecans over them.
Then, powdered sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350°.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp in salty water, seasoned with the garlic and celery tops.
Let water boil adding shrimp.
Boil shrimp for about 15 minutes.
Cut shrimp into 2 or 3 pieces.
Mix thoroughly and add celery, egg, pickle and mayonnaise.
Mix thoroughly and add salt and red pepper to taste.
Serve with lettuce leaves or scraped out tomatoes.

title: double nut fudge
directions: Melt chocolate morsels and chocolate bar in top of a 2-quart double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in sweetened condensed milk, 1/2 cup chopped walnuts, 1/2 cup chopped almonds, the vanilla and salt.
Spread in an 8-inch square wax paper-lined pan.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.

title: green tomato raspberry freezer jam
directions: Mix tomatoes with the sugar; bring to a boil and boil for 20 minutes.
Start with a rolling boil for 5 minutes, then reduce heat for a slow boil and stir every 5 minutes only to blend. Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Stir until the gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into freezer jars.
Cool and freeze.
If canning, do not seal for 24 hours, then seal with melted paraffin. One batch makes 50 ounces.

title: beef and bean soup with pasta
directions: Put water in stock pot.
Bring to boil.
Add salt, meat, bones, onion and bay leaves; simmer 2 hours.
Skim froth as needed during first 15 to 20 minutes of cooking.
Place green beans in saucepan.
Cover with salted water; bring to boil, then cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook vermicelli in boiling salted water as to package directions; drain and cool.
Remove bone from stock; trim fat from meat and set aside.
Strain stock.
Add garlic, string beans and diced meat.
Sprinkle with chives and parsley.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 8.

title: apricot or peach leather
directions: Cook fruit until soft. Puree in blender. Pour on oiled baking pan. Spread out to 1/4-inch and dry in low oven. After puree is dry, pull sheet from pan in a solid layer. Place leather on wax paper dusted with cornstarch or arrowroot to finish drying. Roll up and store.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Bring water to a boil and dissolve gelatin.
Add strawberries with juice, pineapple and bananas.
Pour 1/2 mixture into oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish and chill until firm. Spread sour cream over top.
Pour remaining strawberry mixture over sour cream and let congeal.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Combine the butter, onion, parsley, garlic powder, tarragon and pepper.
Shape mixture into six pencil-thin strips, about 2-inches long.
Place on waxed paper.
Freeze until firm, about 30 minutes.
Flatten each chicken breast to 1/4-inch.
Place one butter strip in the center of each chicken breast.
Fold long sides over butter; fold ends up and secure with a toothpick.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Stir together the sugar, syrup, margarine and salt.
Bring to a boil; turn heat down and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter flavoring and soda; mix well.
It will look odd (that's okay), but stir thoroughly.
Pour over popped corn in a large roasting pan.
Roasted, unsalted almonds can be mixed in, if desired, at this point.
Sit together well, then bake at 250° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring well every 20 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.
Store well (if hidden) in lidded, plastic container.

title: my granny's ranger cookies
directions: Combine shortening, brown sugar, granulated sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; mix well. Mix in remaining items.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until nicely browned and done.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add dressing when ready to serve.

title: alpha bits salad
directions: Cook and drain Alpha Bits.
Drain both oranges and pineapple. Reserve juice and add sugar, salt and flour.
Add eggs that have been beaten with the juices.
Cook on medium heat until thickens. Pour over cooked Alpha Bits.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, fold in fruits and topping; set a few days.
It's better a few days old, up to 2 weeks.

title: mozzarella meat loaf
directions: Mix together, except cheese, and spread on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll up.
Top with more spaghetti sauce.
Seal ends.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain, then add water, onion, pepper, taco seasoning, tomatoes, tomato sauce and sour cream to beef; let simmer about 30 minutes.
Crumble 1/2 of chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Put 1/2 of meat mixture on top of chips. Sprinkle 1/2 cheese on top of meat.
Add remaining chips, meat and cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Serve while hot.

title: mama's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix together the first three ingredients, then fold in Cool Whip.
Let set in the refrigerator until set.

title: party ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cut the rolls in half like for sandwiches. Spread the mixture on the rolls. Cut or tear the ham and cheese into pieces to fit the roll and place a piece of ham and a piece of cheese on each roll. Warm the rolls just until the cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix the meat, soup and milk and heat on top of stove for about 15 minutes (until it bubbles good).
Mix the stuffing with the stick of melted butter.
Put half of the stuffing on the bottom of two 9 x 13-inch baking dishes.
Pour the chicken mixture on top of the stuffing, then put the rest of the stuffing mix on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix everything together and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 pies.

title: breakfast potatoes
directions: Mix potatoes, salt, cheese and onion in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sour cream, soup and melted butter and spread on top.
Then top with 1/4 cup melted butter and 2 cups cornflakes, crushed, sprinkled over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nanny's chess pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; add butter and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to full boil and boil for 1 minute only.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and crunchy peanut butter. Stir until melted.
Add salt and oatmeal.
Drop from spoon on waxed paper to cool.
Shape with fork.

title: frozen parfait
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into parfait or plastic glasses (leaving enough space to add ginger ale when serving). Freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving.

title: fritters
directions: This is a refreshing, easy to take along snack!

title: cal-a-vie roasted garlic and ricotta dip
directions: Roast garlic in covered casserole at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Separate cloves to cool, then squeeze out pulp into bowl of food processor.
Puree, then add remaining ingredients except for herb.
Chill until ready to serve, then stir in chives.
Makes an excellent dip or filling for hors d'oeuvres.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs, milk and 10 tablespoons of water in mixer bowl. Add mixture of sugar, cocoa, flour and salt; blend well.
Stir in butter, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Pour into pie shells.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until pies are set.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Heat oil in large (6 quart) heavy saucepan over medium heat. Add ground meat, onion, green peppers and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently, 20 to 30 minutes or until meat is no longer red and fat has cooked out of meat.
Skim off fat.

title: reese's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 30 (2-inch) foil cupcake liners in small muffin pans or on cookie sheet.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except syrup and chips.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour 3/4 of batter into well greased, floured Bundt pan.
Stir syrup into remaining batter and blend. Pour over batter in pan.
Sprinkle chips on top and marbelize it. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Let cool for 15 to 20 minutes. When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serves 12.

title: shrimp and eggplant jambalaya
directions: Peel and
dice	eggplant; fry in oil.
When tender, add onions, celery, bell
pepper
and
garlic
and
cook for a few minutes.
Add
tomatoes and well washed rice.
Season to taste and let it all cook slowly for 1 hour, adding water if needed. About 20 minutes before serving, add the shrimp and cook until done. Serves 6.

title: apple delight
directions: Spread cream cheese on a plate.
Top with the caramel fudge and cover with chopped nuts.
Core and slice apples in orange or lemon juice to prevent browning.
Arrange apple slices around edge of plate containing the cream cheese, topping and nuts.
Dip apples and enjoy.

title: confetti salad
directions: Drain tuna and set aside.
Boil macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse well with cold water and drain.
Chop and slice vegetables.
Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise and add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on lettuce with fresh tomato slices and rolls.
This is best made ahead for the flavors to blend.

title: sausage a la calato
directions: Cut sausage in 4-inch links. Place in square baking pan. Add onion, potatoes, peas and garlic. Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and bouillon. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until sausage is done. Serves 8.

title: old-fashioned cucumber pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, water and spice.
Bring to a boil; add cucumbers.
Return to boil.
Cook until cucumbers change to dark green.
Put in jars; cover with juice and seal.
Any juice left over may be saved and added to next canning juice.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream oil in sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Cream well.
Add buttermilk and flour with soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well. Bake in three layers at 350° until done.

title: baked vidalia onion
directions: Peel onion.
Add butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Wrap tightly in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops with apple gravy
directions: Cut off excess fat on pork chops. Heat 4 teaspoons butter and oil in skillet and quickly brown each side.

Turn down heat. Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes. Turn each side twice. Melt remaining butter in a saucepan. Stir in chopped apples. Cook on medium heat a few minutes. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons flour over cooking apples. Add milk and half and half.
Add nutmeg, salt and pepper (white pepper preferred). Serve gravy over pork chops.

title: sausage apple balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on baking sheet sprayed lightly with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Watch to make sure bottoms don't burn.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli.
Add all ingredients, except butter and bread crumbs; mix well.
Pour into casserole.
Melt butter; add bread crumbs to make crumb topping.
Put on top of broccoli mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Double recipe for great party dish.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order listed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased
pan.
Sprinkle
box of yellow cake mix over batter.
Drizzle
cup
melted margarine and 1 cup nuts over cake mix.
Bake
in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
When done, knife will come out clean.

title: mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth and creamy.
Shape into balls and flatten with fork.

title: greek salad
directions: Mix ingredients, cover and chill until serving time, up to 2 hours.
Pour Greek dressing over just before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 side dish servings.

title: sausage won tons
directions: Fry sausage until brown, drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Brush wrap lightly with oil on both sides, place wraps in a muffin pan and bake at 350° for five minutes.
Remove from oven and add mixture to wraps and bake five more minutes.

title: best frozen punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add lemon juice, sugar and pineapple juice.
Freeze.
Before serving, thaw and add Mountain Dew and Sprite.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut up in bite size.
Add all other ingredients and cook until thick.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add all remaining ingredients except parsley.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley.

title: vegetable bean salad
directions: In large bowl, fold beans into combined vegetables.
Combine oil, lemon juice and chili powder.
Pour over salad and toss lightly.
Chill several hours.
Serves 12.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and cranberries and let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Mix boiling water and jello, let cool.
Mix all ingredients together and congeal.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add to melted butter and eggs. Stir in dry ingredients until well-blended. Put in greased bowl. Cover and let rise. (Can refrigerate overnight.)

Divide dough in half. Roll out on floured waxed paper. Cut into 12 pie shaped wedges. Roll into shape from wide end to point. Do same with other half. Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise about 1 hour, in warm place. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, flour or cornstarch and salt.
Gradually add milk and unsweetened chocolate.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat and cook and stir 2 minutes.
Separate egg yolks and whites; set whites aside for meringue.
Beat yolks, then gradually stir 1 cup of the hot mixture into yolks.
Return egg mixture to pan; bring to a gentle boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour hot filling in baked pastry shell.
Spread meringue over hot filling.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk corn chowder
directions: In 3 quart saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Save drippings in pan.
Cook onion until tender, but not browned.
Add potatoes, corn, 1 1/2 cups broth, celery, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup broth; add to veggies and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat to low.
Stir in buttermilk and heat through, but do not boil.
Serve in bowls and top with bacon.

title: king chicken casserole
directions: Tear chicken into bite size pieces.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Place a layer of Doritos on bottom of pan just to cover.
Place half of chicken on top.
Make another layer of Doritos, then chicken.
Mix onion, soups and tomatoes.
Pour over chicken layer.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add grated cheese over top and bake 10 minutes more.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix the pineapple juice and soy sauce.
Marinate chicken breasts in mixture for about 15 minutes.
Grill 4 or 5 minutes on each side. Brush with the sweet and sour sauce after they are done.
Place pineapple rings around chicken and serve.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and white sugar.
Fold in grapes.
Pour into bowl and top with mixture of brown sugar and pecans.

title: cherry pecan pie
directions: Stir lemon juice in milk until thick.
Add food coloring to cherries.
Add cherries and pecans to milk mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into vanilla wafer or graham cracker crust and chill.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well, fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Make icing and pour over cake while warm.

title: rice krispies surprises
directions: Heat margarine and marshmallows until melted.
Pour dry Jell-O into marshmallow mixture.
Pour over 6 cups Rice Krispies; mix well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use different color Jell-O for different holidays.

title: texas tacos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain fat.
Add taco seasoning mix (use directions on package) to meat.
Mix well.
Spoon into tortilla shells, roll up and place in greased baking dish.
Cover well with sour cream.
Spread cheese over top of all.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: german chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a greased and floured bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain fat.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Add catsup.
Cook on low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on rolls.

title: home style baked beans
directions: Place 1 pound of beans in a large bowl and cover well with water to which 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda has been added.
Let it stand overnight.
Next day, drain and add fresh water to cover. Cook gently in covered pan until tender, about 1 hour (depending on quality of beans).
When done, drain off excess water, but do not leave beans to dry (leaving about 1/2 cup of the liquid).
Add 1 cup of the catsup to the beans, 4 slices of bacon, salt and pepper. Make a paste with the cornstarch, syrup, 1/4 cup catsup and molasses.
Add all to the beans.
Pour into a well-greased baking dish.
Arrange 6 half slices of bacon over top.
Bake, covered, in a 275° for about 3 hours, removing cover towards end.
If they boil over while baking, keep cover slightly ajar.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet. Cook chicken over high heat for 3 minutes on each side.
Do not cook longer.
Transfer to warm serving platter.
Add chives or green onions, lemon juice, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until sauce is smooth.
Whisk in remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: dip for fruits
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften and mix with an electric beater until smooth and creamy.
Add Marshmallow Fluff and mix well. Allow to stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Serve with fresh fruits.
Apples are our favorite.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Blend strawberries and butter with mixer at high speed.
Blend thoroughly.
Add powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.
Serve with rolls, toast or cookies.

title: mormor's date and nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and soda.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix sugar, butter, egg and vanilla together until creamy.
Mix flour and salt.
Strain juice off dates and add alternately with flour and salt mix.
Add dates and nuts last. Place in 2 well-greased bread pans.
Bake at 325° for one hour or more.
Or, place in 4 small loaf pans and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Serves 24.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside.
Melt butter.
Add flour and milk.
Stir, add cheese and let simmer, until cheese is melted, over low heat.
Add to cooked macaroni.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and applesauce.
Dissolve soda in water and add.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven.

title: artichoke hors d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all ingredients, except extra bread crumbs and extra Parmesan cheese, and roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in remaining bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Freeze if you wish.

title: german white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add soda to buttermilk, then combine alternately with the dry ingredients to the butter-sugar mixture. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Prepare and slice all ingredients.
Cook noodles in salted boiling water.
Drain in colander, run cold water over noodles to remove excessive starch from them.
Reserve.
Place oil in wok, heat to smoking point.
Add chicken, onions and salt, if desired. Stir-fry approximately 3 minutes.
Add celery and bean sprouts (celery cabbage); stir-fry briefly, cover wok and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove cover and add water chestnuts, bamboo shoots, mushrooms and soya sauce.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
(Be sure to lift lid and stir vegetables to keep from sticking to wok.)
When ingredients are cooked to your taste, add more salt and pepper, if desired.
Mix in noodles, cover until noodles are hot.
Serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Mix
in
a
bowl
cake
flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Make
a well then add egg yolks, water or other choices listed, and
oil.
Beat
cup egg whites until stiff but not dry, with 1 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Fold first mixture into second mixture. Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300°
for
45 minutes.
Tube pan may be used.
Then bake at 325° for 60 minutes. Ice with your favorite topping.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Make syrup of vinegar, spices and sugar; pour over fruit while still hot.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil carrots and celery in stock until tender.
Add herbs, spices and bouillon; simmer for 1 hour.
(May need to add water prior to boiling noodles.)
Bring soup to a boil.
Add chicken, mushrooms and noodles.
Cook until noodles are done.
Freezes well, too.

title: chow chow
directions: Grind or chop vegetables; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight, then rinse and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables and heat to boiling.
Simmer for 3 minutes. Pack in jars and seal.
Makes 9 pints.

title: edible birthday card
directions: On standard size poster board write the following message, leaving enough space for the candy bars.
Hot glue candy bars in proper order:
Happy Birthday (Whatchamacallit).
We wanted to give a (100 Grand) but our money slipped through our (Butterfinger) and it isn't (Payday) yet.
We did look on (5th Avenue) to find the right gift, but a pet (Kitkat) you don't need and a space shuttle trip to (Mars) via the (Milky Way) seemed inappropriate.
We wish you (Mounds) of (Almond Joy) as you (Zero) in on another year. Best wishes on your special day.
We promise not to (Snicker) about your age.

title: fudge
directions: Combine fruit well with Alba '66 in small dish.
Freeze. Serves one.

title: hungarian frittata
directions: Cut salami into strips and sausages into slices.
Rinse peppers.
Deseed and cut into strips.
Saute sausages in skillet for 3 minutes.
Add onion and pepper strips.
Saute a few minutes. Add tomatoes.
Reduce heat.
Beat eggs.
Pour eggs over all ingredients in pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until egg mixture is set.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve hot.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Mix thoroughly; add flour and blend.
Spread dough on ungreased 18 x 12-inch sheet.
Brush with unbeaten egg whites. Sprinkle with pecans.
Pat into dough and bake 1 hour at 250°. Cut into strips the size you like while still warm.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In large skillet, cook onions and celery in butter until tender-crisp.
Add remaining ingredients except grated cheese. Spoon into buttered 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 3 minutes longer, or until cheese melts.

title: pork chops and carrots
directions: Cut carrots, slice in half, then again as have quarters. Arrange to cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, salt, thyme and pepper.
Dredge chops in mixture.
Brown.
Arrange over carrots.
Put onion slice on each chop.
Pour water.
Cover pan slightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together in large saucepan vanilla pudding, tapioca pudding, orange Jell-O and water.
Bring to a boil, then cool. Add whipped topping and Mandarin oranges.
Enjoy!

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs until light, then beat in syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla. Melt butter and chocolate together, then cool and stir in. Pour in pie shell and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top should be set, but filling should be somewhat soft inside.
Do not overbake.
Should be like custard.
May add pecans for a chocolate style pecan pie.

title: turkey sausage quiche
directions: Crumble and cook turkey sausage in a nonstick skillet. Add mushrooms and onion. Cook broccoli in microwave for 7 minutes on High. Add broccoli to sausage mixture. Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray and add turkey/vegetable mixture.

title: cheddar garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Stir baking mix, milk and cheese together until soft dough forms. Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Stir together butter and garlic brush over warm biscuits.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown beef with onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add tomato soup and salsa to beef and simmer.
Grate cheese.
Spoon 2 tablespoons beef mixture and 1 tablespoon grated cheese on each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam down in a greased pan.
Pour remaining beef mixture and grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken with almonds
directions: Melt butter. Add all other ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gert's peanut butter fudge #3
directions: Cook butter, sugars and milk until soft ball stage (234° to 240°).
Add cornstarch, dissolve in a little cold water; stir in. Remove from stove immediately and beat well.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in brown sugar.
Cool and then blend in eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until light touch leaves slight imprint.
Cut into squares or bars while warm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg yolks.
Fold in flour.
Shape cookie dough into small balls about the size of a penny.
Bake at 250°.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: About 2 hours before serving, dice zucchini.
Coarsely chop broccoli and spinach.
Cook zucchini, broccoli, oregano and 1/4 teaspoon salt over medium heat in 2 tablespoons hot margarine or butter, stirring frequently, until vegetables are tender-crisp (about 5 minutes).
Add spinach and toss until wilted.
Remove skillet from heat.
In medium bowl with fork, mix Ricotta and eggs; set aside.
Prepare lasagna noodles as label directs.
Drain.

title: chicken drummettes
directions: Combine soy sauce, juice, onion and sugar; stir well and pour over drummettes at least 3 hours (overnight, if time permits). Remove and brown in oil.
After browning, put 1/2 cup of marinade in pan with chicken; cover and simmer 30 minutes, or until tender.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Toss cheese and onion with flour (use waxed paper and save a clean up job).
Spread chicken and peas on bottom of crust and sprinkle with cheese-onion mixture.
Combine and beat eggs, milk, garlic salt and pepper until well mixed (not frothy); pour over the other ingredients in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set and top is lightly browned.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chili-artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: squash cornbread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
This freezes well.

title: kraut casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Heat together sauerkraut and margarine.	Fill greased 1 1/2-quart casserole with alternating layers of meat mixture, kraut and rice.
Mix together milk, sour cream and egg; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: calico salad
directions: Drain all of beans.
Rinse kidney beans.
Mix beans, onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper. Pour over beans.
Let set in refrigerator 12 hours.
Don't cover.

title: quick and easy rhubarb jelly
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar.
Let set to form own juice.
Boil 10 minutes; remove from heat.
Add jello.
Spoon into jars and cover.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Flatten chilies, slice the cheese and layer in a greased 3-quart casserole pan.
Start with chilies and alternate with cheeses (separate or mixed).
Layering until all chilies and cheese are used.

title: baked pinto beans
directions: Fry onions, browning them lightly in fat.
Place cooked pinto beans in casserole.
Add onions.
Brown sugar or molasses, tomatoes and chilies, salt, pepper, oregano and meat.
Bake covered in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Finish baking without cover to brown.

title: good biscuits
directions: Mix together and roll out on a lightly floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter and cook at 400° until light brown.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare spaghetti according to package. Drain.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and cook at 400° until brown on top.

title: mud bug soup
directions: Make a roux with butter and flour; add fish stock and wine. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add rest of seasoning.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Serve as soup or serve with rice.

title: german cream cheese cookies
directions: Set oven for 375°.
Work butter and cheese together until blended.
Gradually stir in sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk and vanilla; stir in flour and mix well.
Put through a pastry tube (star, etc.).
Decorate with red or green sugar for Christmas look.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover the last 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch layer cake pans.
In medium bowl, beat margarine and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add soup.
Add dry ingredients and milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Divide batter into pans.
Bake layers 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool layers in pans 10 minutes. Remove to racks and cool completely.

title: faye's chocolate dessert
directions: Beat egg whites first, then set aside.
Mix all other ingredients, except pecans and vanilla wafers.
Fold in egg whites and pecans.
Cover bottom of buttered dish with half of vanilla wafers.
Pour mix over wafers.
Cover with remaining wafers.

title: peanut butter cup fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter in microwave for 2 minutes, stirring well.
Mix in vanilla and brown sugar.
Add 10x sugar after brown sugar is dissolved.
Mix until like play dough.
Press into 9x13 cake pan.

title: red fox salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients well ahead and chill.
Fry bacon crisp.
Drain.
Crumble wedge tomatoes.
Break lettuce into small bits.
Add onion slivers to lettuce and tomato.
Top with bacon and Blue cheese.
Add dressing to salad and toss.

title: financial management bean pot(served by tightwads)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in casserole or bean pot.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves 10.

title: fruit supreme
directions: Open and drain pineapple and mandarin oranges very good.
Add all ingredients together; mix in sour cream.
Refrigerate and serve.
Keep remaining in refrigerator.

title: great baked chicken
directions: Combine sour cream and egg in a bowl.
Coat breasts in mixture and then bread crumbs.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes. Great for pork chops, too.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash and dry lettuce.
Add onions.
Cover and refrigerate to keep crisp.
In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on a paper towel.
Reduce heat to low.
To drippings in pan, add vinegar, sugar, mustard and pepper, stirring well.
Cook about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Crumble bacon and add to lettuce.
Stir dressing and pour over lettuce.
Toss well.
Sprinkle diced eggs on top and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 10 minute catsup
directions: Cook
tomatoes,
pepper, onion, and celery all together until soft.
Drain
off water overnight.
Then strain through sieve or food
mill.
To
this add sugar, vinegar, spices and salt.
Boil for
10 minutes, pour into bottles and seal.
For hot catsup,
add 1/8 teaspoon red pepper and 1/4 teaspoon dry mustard.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion and celery in large salad bowl.
Break frozen peas apart and layer on top of salad.
Spread mayonnaise on top like frosting, sealing around the edges.
Sprinkle sugar and enough cheese to completely cover mayonnaise.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator overnight (24 hours).
Top with bacon, eggs and any of your favorite toppings.
Do not toss, but scoop to retrieve all layers.

title: philly 3-step cheese cake
directions: At medium speed, mix well eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs and mix.
Pour batter into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until center is set.
Cool for best results. Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide and roll into 2 balls. Refrigerate.
Serve with various kinds of crackers.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Cut apples into quarters. Roll apples up in crescent rolls and place in pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Combine butter, sugar, orange juice and vanilla. Bring to boil and pour over rolls. Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex 7-layer dip(meatless)
directions: *Preferred product to use.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Store in refrigerator.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add peanuts, margarine and salt.
Cook to hard crack on candy thermometer.
Quickly add baking soda.
While stirring, pour into well-greased biscuit pan. Cool, then break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: butter brickle crunch cake
directions: Prepare cake and bake according to directions on the box. While still warm, make holes in cake using the end of a wooden spoon. When cake is cooled, pour caramel topping into each hole. Spread whipped cream on top of cake. Then sprinkle Heath Crunch on top of whipped topping. Enjoy!

title: mother's good ole chocolate cake
directions: Melt margarine with water and cocoa; bring to boil.
Sift together sugar, flour and soda; add buttermilk and eggs.
Mix in hot liquid.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: low calorie jello salad
directions: Combine all and refrigerate.

title: good potatoes
directions: Shake all ingredients in a large Ziploc bag.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Yield:
4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, nuts, baking powder and cinnamon. Set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir only until moistened.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together.
Pour rest of the ingredients together.
Add to egg mixture.
Grease pan well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Bread may split on top.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Puncture top with toothpick.
Pour on glaze.
Makes two loaves.
Glaze is enough for both loaves.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bubbles
directions: Combine and let settle.
Skim off any foam.
Store in refrigerator but allow to warm before using.

title: pudding - sauce
directions: Mix pudding ingredients.
Pour all but 1/2 cup into greased 8 x 8 or 9 x 9 pan.
Bake on 350 about 20 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Sprinkle salt over the top of the mixture, then add the ice.
Set 3 hours.
Drain water off. Mix together sugar, vinegar, turmeric, cloves, mustard seed and celery seed and pour over cucumbers.
Bring to a boiling point, but do not boil.
Fill hot jars and seal.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Chop green onion tops and shred the shaved ham.
Roll tips and ham into a ball with the cream cheese.
You may sprinkle garlic salt in the cream cheese, if desired.

title: braised round steak
directions: Cut steak in serving pieces or in thin strips.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in the hot water.
Dredge meat in flour.
Brown on both sides in shortening.
Add bay leaf, onion, salt and pepper, water with the bouillon cubes, carrots and potatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat 50 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.
(I like to add zucchini the last 15 minutes of cooking time.)

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain off grease and let cool.
Add lettuce, tomato, cheese, onion and mayonnaise; toss slightly.
Add corn chips.
Toss well.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Halve peppers lengthwise, removing stem ends, seeds and membranes. Immerse peppers into boiling water for 3 minutes. Sprinkle inside of pepper with salt. Invert on paper towels to drain.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo. Combine all ingredients and place in lightly greased baking pan. Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: halibut in swiss chard
directions: In small bowl, mix onion, mushrooms, pimiento, rice, pepper sauce, lemon juice, soy sauce, oil, honey and ginger root.
Trim stems from Swiss chard and place 1 leaf on piece of foil.
Place 1 fish fillet on the leaf and spread 1/3 cup of rice mixture over the fish.
Start at that end and roll the chard and fish, then roll that roll up in the foil.
Repeat with remaining fillets and place them in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: country sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain and leave.
Put 2 tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
Saute onion and flour in reserved grease until brown.
Add remaining sausage and tomatoes, corn and sugar; mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In 9-inch glass pie pan melt butter, then add sugar and cinnamon.
Stir.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix. Add separated rolls. Arrange in a circle.
Turn over each roll so it is coated.
Bake in microwave 2 minutes with plastic wrap over them.
Using oven mitts, remove plastic wrap and turn rolls over.
Bake another 2 minutes with plastic wrap over them.
Cool and serve.

title: sweet n sour franks
directions: Melt all ingredients except franks in saucepan.
Add franks. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on toothpicks.
