title: crab dip
directions: Dissolve gelatine in water.
Bring
tomato soup to boil and add gelatine mixture.
Combine
cream
cheese, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice
and mix.
Add celery and onion.
Add tomato soup mixture.
Drain
crab
juice
and fold into mixture.
Pour into mold and chill overnight.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel oranges, removing all outside membrane.
Cut in thin slices.
Place alternate layers of oranges, coconut and sugar in serving dish.
Sprinkle with sherry flavoring.
Press down with plate; chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and boil for 5 minutes.

title: beduhns' dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add milk and egg; mix.
Roll into balls on a floured board.
Place on hot sauerkraut and cook, covered, on stove.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag for shaking.
Moisten potatoes with water.
Shake a few at a time in bag, coating potatoes well.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place potatoes in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once during baking.

title: peanut butter apple dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first four ingredients; mix well.
Serve with apples.
Store in the refrigerator.
Yields 2 2/3 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all wet ingredients.
Add all dry ingredients, except flour. Add flour last and slowly.
Pour into 3 large pans or 5 small pans.
Fill only half full.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: italian zucchini diabetic recipe
directions: In a greased 2 1/2 quart casserole, layer 1/3 of the zucchini, onion and tomatoes.
Squeeze 1 lemon, quartered, over all. Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning and 1/4 teaspoon red pepper flakes.
Repeat layers.
Dot with margarine.
Squeeze remaining lemon over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350° or until vegetables are done.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain. Return to pot and add 2 tablespoons margarine and 1/2 cup milk. In large saucepan, melt remaining 6 tablespoons margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add remaining milk, all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Stir in gravy, chicken and noodles.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan or large casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dublin potato salad
directions: Combine vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed; set aside.

title: cheese 'n beef crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In frying pan, brown ground beef and green pepper; drain.
Stir in seasoning, tomato paste and water. Simmer 10 minutes.
Arrange 8 triangles of rolls in ungreased pie pan over sides to form crust.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan over crust.
Spoon 1/2 of hot meat mixture onto crust.
Top with 2 slices Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon remaining over cheese and top with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese (put this on before baking).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut remaining cheese slices into lengthwise strips arranging in lattice pattern.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Slice butter into pats and place in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Pour flour mixture into dish and spoon fruit on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Blend butter and sugar in bowl.
Stir in egg yolk and vanilla. Sift flour and salt into bowl.
Mix well.
Chill.
Roll in balls. Dip in slightly beaten egg white and roll in nuts.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven.
After 5 minutes, press thumb in center of each cookie.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool. Fill with frosting and garnish with peanut M&M's.
Use red and green ones for Christmas.
Use Confectioners Sugar Icing.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Squeeze lemons and dissolve sugar in juice.
Slice one lemon very thinly .
Beat cream until thick, but not stiff.
Combine all ingredients and freeze.

title: mini pizza
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until done; drain well.
Add cheese and melt.
Butter and toast bread.
Spoon mixture on bread; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Put under broiler until cheese melts.
You can freeze for later use.

title: stuffed steak rolls
directions: Cook up steaks.
Let drain on paper towels. Make stuffing according to package.
Spoon stuffing onto steaks.
Roll up and put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cook up au jus gravy mix according to package.
Pour over rolls.
Cover pan with foil.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Put crushed pineapple in bottom of long cake pan.
Spread pie filling over it.
Sprinkle cake mix all over it.
Slice margarine. Place over cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: romaine mandarin orange salad
directions: Blend the lettuce, oranges, avocado and toasted almonds.
Add sauce just before serving.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: In a large bowl, combine berries, sugar, cornstarch, and cinnamon. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish that has been sprayed with a non-stick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes stirring after about 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place boned, cooked chicken in casserole dish.
Put cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Stir together remaining ingredients. Pack dressing on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain and chop.
Mix hot, cooked rice with cheese, onion and butter so that it blends, then fold in spinach. Turn into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Simmer the giblets in 1 quart of water until tender; drain (save liquid) and chop fine.
With 1/2 cup of drippings, blend 6 tablespoons flour, add the liquid in which the giblets were cooked plus enough hot water to make a thin gravy.
Cook for 5 minutes. Add the chopped giblets and boiled egg.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve over turkey and dressing.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well and pour into Bundt pan (well-greased and floured).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Brown ground beef.
Remove seeds from chilies.
Cut lengthwise and place in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with meat and grated cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, flour, salt, Tabasco and pepper. Beat until smooth.
Pour over meat and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: hamwich
directions: Mix ham, eggs, onion, cheese, mayonnaise and chili sauce. Spread on sandwich rolls and wrap in aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mixed greens
directions: Boil meat in 2 quarts water for 1 hour.
In meantime, prepare greens, removing stems and damaged leaves.
Wash 3 or 4 times until rinse water is clear.
Mustard and turnip green leaves are small and do not require cutting before cooking.
Add whole leaves and seasoning to boiling water.
Cover and cook rapidly for about 25 minutes or until tender.
When done, cut greens with knife while still in pot.
Serve with hot pepper slices and vinegar.

title: homemade doughnuts
directions: Scald milk and chill.
Drain potatoes and mash.
Mix with milk.
Put Crisco in 1 cup hot potato water.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast.
Put vanilla and sugar in milk mixture.
Add eggs to potato water.
Add salt and combine potato water and milk mixture. Add flour.
Knead.
Cover in pan and let rise for 2 hours.
Work down.
Cut doughnuts.
Fry in hot grease.
Mix remaining ingredients and glaze.

title: lime pie
directions: Fold all together and pile into 2 crusts.
Chill.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Prepare meatballs with first 9 ingredients (except add parsley before mixing); then shape into 1-inch balls.
Cook meatballs in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat about 15 minutes, turning occasionally until brown.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain potatoes; add sour cream, oleo, cheese and bacon (crumbled in small pieces).
Salt and pepper to desired taste.

title: curried rice
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Melt butter in heavy skillet. Add onion and saute for 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is tender but not mushy.
Add rice, raisins, almonds, curry powder, salt and pepper. Fold to blend well.
Serve garnished with fresh mint or parsley.

title: yellow rock candy
directions: Melt margarine; add peanut butter and graham cracker crumbs. Mash into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: skillet beef casserole(6 servings)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water to cover for 3 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Drain and set aside.
Trim fat from steak; cut steak into 1-inch pieces.
Coat a 10-inch ovenproof skillet with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add steak; cook, turning occasionally, until browned on all sides. Remove from pan; set aside.
Wipe drippings from skillet with a paper towel.
Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Add carrot; saute 4 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add onion, celery and garlic; saute until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour, pepper and thyme; stir well.
Stir flour mixture into vegetable mixture. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add beef, green beans, tomatoes and vegetable juice cocktail.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil the chicken in water seasoned with onion, celery, salt and pepper until tender.
Remove chicken from stock; bring stock to boil.
Drop dumplings in; add hard-boiled egg.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove skin and bones from chicken.
Return to broth. Cook until dumplings are tender.

title: dried bean soup
directions: Soak 2 quarts of white beans overnight.
Cut 2 pounds of beef up and along with bones put in a soup pot with a pound of bacon. Bring to boil and skim off scum.
Add a little celery and pounded celery seed.
Cook until all is done and then strain through colander.
Enjoy.

title: microwave turkey-stuffed peppers
directions: Stand peppers in a 9-inch microwave-safe pie dish.
Add 2 tablespoons water to dish.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes until crisp-tender.
Meanwhile, put turkey, salsa, tomato sauce, rice, chili powder, cumin and garlic in a large bowl.
Mix until blended.

Fill peppers with turkey mixture. Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 16 to 18 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every 4 minutes, until thermometer inserted in center of turkey mixture registers 160° and peppers are tender. Remove peppers from oven and let stand 5 minutes to finish cooking.

title: texas cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Add 1/4 cup of sugar and toss.
Combine remaining ingredients and remaining sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour immediately over vegetable mixture.
Cover and chill for about 4 hours.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage slowly until crumbly. Drain and blot.
Set aside.
Make a white sauce with butter and flour, stirring over low heat until smooth and pasty.
Gradually add milk, stirring till thickened.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in crumbled sausage.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot biscuits, grits or toast.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken (boil).
While chicken is cooking, prepare Stove Top as directed on box; set aside.
After chicken is done, tear chicken off the bones and place in casserole dish.
Add soup to chicken and mix.
Put Stove Top on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot devil potatoes
directions: Prepare packaged potatoes according to directions to serve 4. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into 4 foil baking shells. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked spareribs
directions: Cut ribs in rather small pieces, about 3 or 4 inches. Marinate in chicken broth, soy sauce, vinegar, honey, sherry, ginger and garlic.
Stir completely.
Put ribs in and marinate for 3 hours (no longer, or ribs will become tough).
Bake for 2 1/4 hours at 325°.
Baste every 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Bring beans to boil in large pan.
Boil for 10 minutes. Drain.
Pour cold water over them immediately until cool.
Put grease in large skillet and let it get hot.
Mix vinegar, sugar and water separately in another container.
Add beans and mixture in hot grease and let simmer 15 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Combine and mix well.
Marinate meat 4 to 12 hours in refrigerator.
May baste with marinade during cooking.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix by hand and pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together; put in greased baking dish. Mix other ingredients and sprinkle over top of potato mixture. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: buckwheat pancakes
directions: Thin the batter with milk or water for the desired thickness of your pancakes.

title: coffee ice cream punch
directions: Heat coffee, sugar and water to dissolve.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add to remaining ingredients and mix well.
Yields 50 servings.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix and sift flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and soda into a large mixing bowl.
Stir in mayo.
Gradually stir in water and vanilla until smooth and blended.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into bottom of 14-inch pizza pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400° until golden; cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix spaghetti and tuna.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs and cheese on top.
Place in casserole dish and put in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Mix together white sauce, salmon, egg yolks, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Beat egg white very stiff; fold into mixture. Pour into casserole dish or souffle dish sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° until brown and toothpick comes out clean. Approximately 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan the pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle box of cake mix over the pineapple and cherries.
Cut butter up over top in rows.
Sprinkle on pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
You can use sliced peaches instead of pineapple and cherries and layer with butter and brown sugar alternately.

title: country brunch
directions: Trim crusts from bread and cut slices in half.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer as follows:
1/2 of bread, 1/2 of ham, 1/2 of each of cheeses.
Repeat layers.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Pour over layers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Combine cornflakes and melted butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil to prevent overbrowning.
Let stand 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: crispix senbei
directions: Cook
the
margarine,
sugar, oil, Karo syrup and shoyu until it	comes to a boil.
Pour the mixture over the Crispix and peanuts.
Sprinkle the nori and mix well.
Bake in oven at 250° for
minutes.
Mix
well and then bake additional 30 minutes. Good anytime!

title: chocolate surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix together flour, 2 cups of sugar, cocoa, 1 teaspoon of salt and soda.
Add oil, water, vinegar and vanilla.
Fill cupcake paper with mixture to 2/3 full.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour with the buttermilk.
Add dissolved chocolate and vanilla, then fold in the egg whites.
Cook in four layers at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Prepare casserole by buttering top and sides.
Put in a layer of bread cubes, dots of butter, chopped onion, salt and pepper, 1 tablespoon flour and half of the tomatoes.
Repeat process.
Cook in 350° oven.
Cover, cooking for first 1/2 hour and then remove cover for last 1/2 hour.
Pan under casserole for soiling oven.

title: deep dish pizza pie
directions: Place 1 pie crust in 9 inch pie pan. Mix together all ingredients, pour into pie pan. Place the second crust over filling. Flute edges. Cut slits in top. Bake at 425 for 35 to 45 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: delicious meat loaf
directions: Mix together the ground meat, evaporated milk, oats, chopped onion, salt and pepper.
Cook the tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, chili powder and 1/2 teaspoon of salt for 5 minutes.
Stir half of this mixture into the meat loaf and place in loaf pan.
Pour rest of sauce over the top and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: In a shallow container (pizza pan or cookie sheet)

Spread: 2 cans refried beans, and 2 or 3 avacodoes mashed with 1 tbsp. lemon juice. Mix together: 1 c. mayonnaise, 1 c. sour cream, & 1 pkg. taco seasoning. Spread over the avacodoes: 3 c. shredded cheddar cheese, 2 chopped tomatoes, 1 bunch green onions chopped up, & 1 can sliced ripe olives.

title: cheese-filled chicken cutlets
directions: Pound chicken breasts to about 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut in serving size pieces.
On waxed paper, mix salt with 3 tablespoons flour.
Coat chicken cutlets with flour mixture.

title: hawaiian ham steaks
directions: Cut each ham steak into three serving sized pieces.
Combine brown sugar and mustard; spread over ham.
Top each piece of ham with a pineapple slice.
Place in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until heated through.

title: tortellini alfredo
directions: Cook tortellini 5 minutes less than directed on package. Drain.
Cook Alfredo Sauce, using more milk than directed.
When sauce is thickened, add peas, ham and drained tortellini.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.

title: toasted cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread and beat well.
Trim crusts from bread.
Using two slices of bread, spread mixture between slices and on top and sides.
Cut into fourths.
Place in refrigerator for several hours before baking.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Can be frozen.

title: minnie kyttle's devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs and beat well. Add melted chocolate and mix thoroughly.
Add milk and mix.
Add flour, baking soda and salt, sifted together.
Mix.
Makes three 9-inch layers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind the 2 meats together; add rest of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Last 15 minutes, baste with 4 tablespoons of brown sugar and 3 tablespoons of mustard, mixed together.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Before serving, add combined olive oil and vinegar.
The Blue cheese gives it some zing; can add Cheddar if you want.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Drain berries.
Add water to juice to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Add to gelatin.
Chill until partially set.
Whip until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip and berries. Fold in cake.
Pour into shallow pan.
Chill until firm.
This will make 2 large pans.

title: salsa dip
directions: Blend together in blender.
Let sit for several hours for best flavor.
In a pinch, can be served immediately.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in casserole dish. Cover with Topping.

title: *rice pilaf with meat
directions: Brown meat mixture in same pan you will prepare rice.
Remove all fat and add rice, seasoning packets and 2 1/2 cups water. Cook on low until mixture is 3/4 done. Add butter or margarine and work through rice.
Finish cooking.
Let sit with paper towel under lid so as not to have mixture retain too much moisture.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Sift flour over fruits and nuts and mix well.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, lemon extract and floured fruits.
Mix well. Bake in stem pan at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the pumpernickel loaf at least 1 hour before serving. Keep refrigerated until serving.
Put in cut out round of pumpernickel loaf.

title: mexican turkey and dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cornbread mixture, butter and water in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Spread half of mixture into a greased 11 x 14-inch baking dish.

title: rice jardin
directions: Saute onion and zucchini in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Prepare apples and celery (leave skins on apples).
Combine apples and pour the pineapple syrup.
Toss.
Add pineapple, celery, walnuts and raisins.
Mix and chill.
Serve in a lettuce lined bowl.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Combine rinds and salt solution.
Cover and soak overnight. Drain and rinse well.
Cook rinds in water until tender.
Drain. Mix remaining ingredients in deep stainless steel pot and bring to boil, making sure all sugar is dissolved.
Add rinds and remove from heat immediately. Fill sterile jars 1 1/2-inches from top with rinds.
Pour syrup mixture over to 1/2-inch from top.
Seal and process in hot water bath 5 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Check for sealing before storage.
Makes approximately 4 pints.

title: miracle beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in roasting pan; cover closely and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into a ball and chill for at least 3 hours.
Cover ball with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: pan de elote(mexican spoon bread)
directions: In a bowl, combine corn, Bisquick, egg, butter, sugar and milk.
Mix well with fork.
Turn half the batter in a well-greased 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Spread chilies evenly over batter, then cover with sliced cheese.
Spread remaining batter over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Using large skillet, melt butter; add oil, half of the parsley, garlic powder, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add shrimp, tossing gently.
Arrange in skillet in single layer.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until tender.
Sprinkle with rest of parsley and serve with lemon wedges.

title: oatmeal pecan pie
directions: Mix melted butter, eggs, syrup, sugar and oats. Pour into crust.
Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake on cookie sheet.

title: italian garden pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain and rinse under cold water.
In small bowl, combine vinegar, oil, dill weed, salt, mustard, pepper and garlic.
In large bowl, combine cooked macaroni, tomato, zucchini, olives and onions.
Pour dressing over salad mixture; toss well to combine ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour to blend flavors. Yields 12 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together with mixer cream cheese and picante sauce. Spread on meat platter.
Sprinkle over with cheese, lettuce, pepper, tomato and onion.
Serve cold with round tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line muffin tin with muffin papers.
Beat egg.
Stir in milk, oil, pumpkin and 1/2 cup raisins (if desired). Stir in remaining ingredients all at once just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Sprinkle tops with sugar before baking, if desired.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Immediately remove from pans.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat ingredients for at least 6 to 8 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Wash zucchini, remove seed and pithy parts, but leave on rind when grinding.
Combine zucchini and onion; stir in pickling salt and let stand overnight.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook fryer (save broth).
Debone and let cool.
Brown bell pepper, onions, pimento and mushrooms in butter.
Boil spaghetti in broth (save broth again).
Pour cooked spaghetti in large, shallow pan.
Add sauteed ingredients and tomatoes (which have been cut up).
Mix.
Add enough broth until juicy.
Sprinkle with spaghetti sauce mix.
Add grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Makes a large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Can be frozen very well.

title: new potato, kielbasa and gruyere salad
directions: Cook the potatoes in large saucepan of boiling water until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Peel, if desired, and slice. Transfer to a large bowl.
Gently mix in vinegar and green onions. Use a rubber baker's scraper.
Cool.
Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, horseradish and caraway.
Mix into potatoes.
Add kielbasa and cheese.
Line plates with the radicchio.
Spoon atop salad. Add pepper to taste.
Serve with hot, crusty French bread.

title: lemon loaves
directions: Spray and flour two 9 x 5-inch or 6 mini loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add milk, rind and juice. Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Slowly add to batter.
Mix well.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours until lightly browned (do toothpick test).
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans. Glaze.

title: vegetable quiche squares
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with pie crusts.
Sprinkle vegetables, cheese and bacon over crust.
Beat remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting. Yields 24 appetizer squares.

title: potato soup duos
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over a medium heat, saute onion in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add water, bouillon and potatoes.
Bring to a boil; cover and cook gently until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
In two batches, blend until smooth in an electric blender.
Return to saucepan and use as a base for one of the following soups:

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg and molasses and combine well.
Sift dry ingredients together, then add slowly to your shortening mixture.
After all ingredients are combined, roll into small balls the size of a walnut and roll in granulated sugar before placing on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
These cookies will puff up and crack a bit, then settle down.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook Minute rice, chicken and broccoli.
In 9 x 12-inch pan, put layer of rice, then layer of broccoli, then layer of chicken, then layer of grated sharp cheese.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, lemon juice and mayo together, add water to make 2 cups.
Pour this mixture over cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lime fluff
directions: Mix juice from pineapple with Jell-O as part of liquid; chill and
let set. Mix in crushed pineapple, drained, and the cottage cheese, Cool Whip and the Grape-Nuts.

title: dilled carrot soup(6 servings)
directions: Heat butter and oil in large soup pot.
Saute leeks until soft.
Add carrots and potatoes and saute 5 minutes more.
Add chicken stock and bring to simmer.
Add thyme and bay leaf and cook until vegetables are tender (30 to 40 minutes).
Remove bay leaf.
Puree in food processor or blender in batches.
Add remaining seasonings.
If soup is too thick, add chicken stock. Serve hot or very cold and garnish with finely chopped fresh dill just before serving.

title: dried peaches
directions: Slice green tomatoes thick.
Place slices in jars.
Put 1 teaspoon salt in each quart jar or 1/2 teaspoon for pints.
Cover with cold water to 1/2 inch of the top and seal.
Boil in hot water bath for 20 minutes.
When ready to use, drain, dip each piece in flour and fry in skillet of hot shortening or oil.
Turn once.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with slices of cheese.
Combine soup and wine.
Mix well. Spoon mixture evenly over chicken.
Combine dry stuffing mix with margarine.
Sprinkle over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix well and pour into a well-greased floured pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake a little longer than 30 minutes at 350°.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Mix soy sauce and vinegar.
Layer chicken in pan and cover with sauce.
Sprinkle garlic atop.
Cut lemons into quarters and squeeze juice over chicken.
Place slices on top.
Add pepper to taste.
Marinate 1 to 2 days.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Last 5 to 10 minutes, brush with barbecue sauce.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish in 350° oven.
Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar and 3/4 cup milk.
Pour into melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Pour peaches and sugar mixture onto batter.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for one hour in preheated oven.
Works with other fruit, too.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar; beat until well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in Nestle chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: green mint cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar and salt. Add sugar a little at a time.
Add food coloring.
Fold in chips. Heat oven to 350° and turn off.
Drop onto foil-lined pan by teaspoonful.
Leave in overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings, spaghetti mix, salt and pepper.
Boil lasagna until tender.
In a large baking dish or pan, put a layer of meat, then lasagna, then your 2 kinds of cheese.
Repeat until ingredients are gone.
Bake at 300° to 350° until cheese has melted.
Ready to serve.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Fold all other ingredients into jello mixture that has slightly thickened.
Let set until firm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: li hing mui ice cake
directions: You will need 1 dozen small decorated paper cups.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Use any cake mix.
Add egg and Cool Whip.
Roll into balls and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: picnic parmesan chicken
directions: Stir together bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, paprika, garlic salt, pepper and parsley.
Dip chicken pieces in butter and then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken on greased baking sheet and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
May be served warm or cold.

title: meat and macaroni casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish layer macaroni, ground beef and corn.
Empty soup and garlic powder and onion into saucepan.
Heat adding 1/4 cup water.
Pour contents of pan over macaroni mixture. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar.	Beat in eggs, one
at a time.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: mama's manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray 13X9-inch dish with cooking spray. Cook shells according to pkg. directions, drain and rinse with cool water. Let dry on paper towels.

title: citrus rice salad
directions: Combine orange sections, rice, 1/4 ounce almonds, onion, bell pepper and raisins.
Set aside.
In small bowl, combine orange juice, vinegar, lime juice, oil, orange peel and white pepper. Pour over rice mixture and toss to coat.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with rest of almonds.

title: frisco club sandwich
directions: Boil the forehead, ears, feet and nice scraps trimmed from the hams of a freshly butchered pig until the meat will almost fall off the bones.
Put this in a large chopping bowl.
(Be sure all bones are removed.)

Season with pepper, salt, sage and summer savory. Chop meat rather coarsely; put it in the same container it was boiled in with just enough of the broth to prevent its burning; warm it thoroughly, mixing it well together.
Now put it into a muslin bag.
Press the bag between two flat surfaces with a heavy weight on top.
When cold and solid, it can be cut in slices. (Good cold or warmed up in vinegar.)

title: almond-lemonade tea
directions: Stir until sugar dissolves. Yields 2-quarts.

title: cream of broccoli soup(low-fat)
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in saucepan; cover and bring to boil.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat and blend in blender until smooth.
Melt oleo in saucepan; stir in flour.
Slowly stir in milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add blended broccoli mixture and heat to boil. Remove from heat and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: penna. dutch macaroni salad
directions: Pour hot macaroni over other ingredients.
Mix.
Pour dressing over top. Mix.

title: kevin's apple cake
directions: Heavily grease (cooking spray works well) a tube pan and coat with cinnamon-sugar mixture (4 tablespoons sugar and 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon).
Reserve leftover cinnamon and sugar.
Peel and cut up 6 apples (small pieces).
Coat with remaining cinnamon-sugar and set aside.

title: white castle hamburger
directions: Mix dry onion and hot water; set aside.
Mix ground round, baby food and broth.
Refrigerate meat mixture for 2 hours before cooking.
Fry meat mixture in skillet.
Punch holes in meat with spatula.
Put onion mixture on patties and turn over and let cook. Cut hot dog buns in half and put patty in between and enjoy.

title: slow death by brownies
directions: Put rack in middle of oven.
Preheat at 350°.
Butter and flour an 11 1/2 x 17 1/4 baking pan (jelly roll pan).

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook green pepper, tomato and onion in hot butter until tender.
Stir in cooked rice, water, salt and pepper.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix fruit, milk, lemon juice and nuts.
Pour mix in pie shell. Slice bananas over filling.
Sprinkle bananas with lemon juice. Top with Cool Whip.

title: spanish rice dish
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck; mix all ingredients except 1/2 c. cheese; Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onions, celery, peppers and green peas.
Mix Hellmann's mayo and sugar. Spread between layers; top with shredded cheese and bacon bits.

title: oven baked shrimp
directions: Take heads off shrimp and leave shell and tails.
Cut onion and garlic; then add margarine, crab boil, salt and pepper together in a pan.
Put in oven and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Bring to boiling stage, water and sugar.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Freeze and serve in highball glass with sours or ginger ale to taste.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream peanut butter and sugar; add beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Prepare cornbread according to package directions.
Crumble into a mixing bowl; add green pepper, onion and tomato.
Mix well then add dressing and mayonnaise.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients including sugar.
Make a well in the middle of dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Divide in 3 loaf pans or 4 (1-pound) coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pans.

title: marinated pot roast with vegetables
directions: Pierce roast with a fork in several places; sprinkle with pepper.
Combine dressing, vinegar and browning-and-seasoning sauce in a 4-quart casserole with lid.
Add roast; turn to coat. Cover and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours, turning twice.

title: low-fat chicken and noodles
directions: Spray skillet with nonfat spray.
Cut chicken into small cubes; fry in skillet until done.
Put soup in pan.
Add diced onions and 3 cans of water.
Bring to a boil and cook until onions are almost done.
Add chicken and rotini noodles.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: coke salad
directions: Mix cherries, sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add cherry jello.
Mix in the next 3 ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish and let chill until firm.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package directions.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats.

title: pickled squash
directions: Soak squash and salt for 3 hours.
Drain.
Add onions and pepper; set aside.
Bring to boil the vinegar, sugar, mustard and turmeric.
Put the first mixture into pint jars; pour boiling mixture on top.
Seal with can flat and rings.

title: orange chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; make well in center.
In small bowl, combine sugar, milk, egg, orange juice, butter and orange rind; mix until blended.
Add to well in flour mixture; stir until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Spoon into greased muffin cups, filling each about 3/4 full.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; save broth to cook noodles.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture may need a little of the chicken broth added if it appears too thick.
Save enough cheese to sprinkle on top.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: tuna roll
directions: Blend 2 tablespoons
of parsley with other ingredients. Blend well.
Shape into 2 rolls and roll in parsley.
Wrap and freeze. Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving.

title: fish creole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake fish 10 minutes, covered.
Combine vegetables, tomato sauce and chili powder in a saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes adding a little water if necessary.
Take fish out of oven and flake.
Add vegetables. Top with herbs. Return to oven to simmer.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone.
Mix melted oleo with stuffing mix.
Reserve a few crumbs for top.
Layer in casserole as follows:
1/2 stuffing mix, 1/2 chicken and 1 can mushroom soup, mixed with 1 cup broth.
Layer again and use chicken soup with broth.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chili sauce
directions: Scald, peel, core and crush tomatoes.
Add all ingredients together in a large, heavy pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Spoon into hot, sterile jars and seal/process according to manufacturer's directions or with wax. Makes about 12 quarts.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add flour, stirring until mixture becomes foamy, but not brown. Add milk; continue stirring to insure smoothness.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Can be doubled depending on amount of potatoes.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat ingredients until smooth.
Spread on serving dish.
Top with shredded lettuce, cubed tomatoes, black olives and sharp Cheddar cheese.
Serve with Doritos.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Pour melted oleo over broccoli and cool.
Mix eggs, cottage cheese, broccoli and oleo mixture.
Stir in corn muffin mix and bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spinach frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in large skillet with heat resistant handle.
Add onion; saute for 5 minutes.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well with fork.
Pour into skillet with onion.
Cook over low heat for about 3 to 5 minutes or until eggs are set around outside.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes or until top is set.
With spatula, loosen from bottom and around edges.
Slide onto serving platter.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Saute
onion,
celery
and bell pepper in butter.
Cook rice, combine with other ingredients.
Put in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: Disjoint chicken wings; discard tips.
Blend soy sauce, scallions, sugar, oil, garlic and ginger in large mixing bowl. Stir in chicken pieces; cover and marinate 30 minutes.
Remove chicken; reserve marinade.
Place chicken side by side in shallow baking pan, skin side down.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn pieces over; baste with reserved marinade and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: bud's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain well.
Add all remaining ingredients except beans.
Simmer 20 minutes, covered.
Add Mexican chili beans and simmer 30 minutes, covered.
Remove cover and cook 15 minutes.
Ready to serve.
Enjoy!

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in hot oil in a large skillet.
Add ground beef; cook until browned.
Stir to crumble.
Add next 8 ingredients, cover and simmer 1 hour; stir occasionally.

title: better than potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir into rice.
Cover and chill.
Stir remaining ingredients in before serving.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in skillet. Saut mushrooms until tender and set aside. Place rice in a 2-quart casserole dish. Add hot chicken broth, water chestnuts, salt and remaining 2 tablespoons butter (cut into small pieces). Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir in sauted mushrooms; cover and continue to bake for 20 to 30 minutes longer or until moisture is absorbed.

title: polynesian fish
directions: Skin, bone and cut fish into 6 serving size pieces.
Place in greased baking dish; pour lime juice on top of fish.
Allow to marinate a few minutes on each side; discard juice.
Pour on melted butter and seasoning.
Broil for 10 minutes, about 4 inches from heat, basting once with butter.
Remove from heat; baste again with pan juices.
Set aside to cool slightly.
Combine the soup and sour cream; spoon on each piece of fish.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes; garnish with onion and shrimp.

title: microwave sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough.
Otherwise, just rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in a microsafe dish or pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped parsley, chives or sage.
Microwave at High power for 10 minutes.
Rearrange them after 5 minutes.
Let rest for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave for another 4 to 6 minutes on High until cheeses are melted and potatoes are soft.
Sprinkle with salt.
Serve potatoes as a side dish or as a main dish with just a salad.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine drained and thawed beans into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Add can of soup, pepper and one-half of the onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated and bubbling lightly.
Top with remaining onions.
Serve immediately.

title: good and easy chicken
directions: Spray baking pan with oil.
Put chicken in pan after it has been
seasoned
with
salt.
Smear chicken liberally with yogurt. Season
again
with
salt.
Cover
chicken with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: luckie creole cabbage
directions: Chop onion and bell pepper. Saute with bacon. Add cabbage and vinegar. Simmer on medium heat for 20 minutes. Add tomatoes and cayenne pepper. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until crumbly.
Add milk slowly to make a stiff dough.
Knead on floured board 1/2 the dough.
Roll out dough to make large oval or rectangle 1/8 to 1/16-inch thick.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; add bananas, cream thoroughly, add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients; add dry ingredients to mixture and beat at medium speed.
Add nuts.
Bake in well-greased and floured bread pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: one-step lasagna(microwave)
directions: Brown meat.
Season with Italian seasoning or oregano, chili powder, salt and pepper, if you are using plain tomato sauce.
Add sauce and mix well.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and mix well.
Add molasses, hot water, flour, spices, soda and salt; mix well.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 9 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: potato pan rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine 2 c. flour, sugar, yeast and salt.
In a saucepan heat water and butter to 120 - 130 degrees.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in mashed potatoes and enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Divide into 16 pieces.
Shape each into a ball, place in two greased 8 or 9 inch round baking pans.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional flour.
Bake at 400° for 18 - 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans to wire racks to cool.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Frost cooled cake or cupcakes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bones.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Arrange in baking dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Cover with remaining ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; mix oil with sugar.
Add eggs (one at a time); beat
after each.
Add dry ingredients to mix.
Stir in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: cocktail meatballs with sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into cocktail size balls. Place in large baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove and drain on paper towels.

title: strawberry honey
directions: Cook water and sugar together for 7 minutes.
Add crushed berries and boil for 5 minutes.
Add powdered alum and remove from heat.
Pour into jars and seal.
Freeze.

title: hot spice tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in a canister.
Mix 2 teaspoons mixture and hot water for drink.

title: chicken cordon bleu (light)
directions: Pound chicken breasts until about 1/4-inch thick.
On top of each place a slice of ham and 1/4 of cheese.
Roll up chicken, tucking in ends, and secure with toothpick.
This can be done ahead and refrigerated until ready to cook.
Spray pan with vegetable oil and brown rolls on all sides.
Sprinkle with thyme and pour broth over rolls.
Cover tightly and simmer 15 minutes. Remove breasts and keep warm, saving pan juices.
Add wine and lemon juice and boil down sauce until reduced by half.
Add pepper. Serve on chicken roll.
Contains 191 calories, 8 grams of fat and 100 mg. cholesterol per serving.

title: veal marsala
directions: Dredge veal through flour seasoned with salt and pepper. Place in a frying pan coated with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Lightly brown veal on both sides; then add remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat for about 15 minutes.
Serve with parsley potatoes.

title: squash patties
directions: Beat egg well.
Add buttermilk and onion and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.
Fry until golden brown.

title: chinese noodle dish
directions: Saute celery and onions; set aside.
Brown meat and combine with celery and onions.
Add other ingredients.
Place in greased baking pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken and dice.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs, and put into a casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Melt oleo and add with eggs to mixture, beating slightly.
Add buttermilk and continue to beat. Add vanilla.
Pour into pastry shells and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until pie is firm from center to edges.

title: zesty broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine soup, cheese, eggs, milk, mayonnaise and horseradish.
Stir in broccoli.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pap's potato casserole
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish.
Stir all ingredients except last two.
Take cornflake crumbs and mix with 1/4 cup melted butter. Top ingredients with cornflake crumbs and bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Perfect for family get togethers.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Combine all ingredients except fruit and pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Add fruit and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss together chicken, celery, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Mix in mayonnaise.
Carefully fold in hard-cooked eggs.

title: chili
directions: In dutch oven or 5 quart pot. Brown meat with pam until done. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic. Stir vegetables and remaining ingredients
in pot. Cook on low for 3 hours covered.

title: banana muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; then add eggs and beat.
In a separate bowl mix all dry ingredients.
Then add dry ingredients and mix alternately.
Add bananas and vanilla.
Mix. Put in muffin tins and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: weight watcher jello
directions: Heat Jell-O and pineapple.
Stir in buttermilk and Cool Whip. Refrigerate until set.

title: johnnie marzette
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add next 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add last 2 ingredients and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: frito pie
directions: Choose "side meat" with a streak of lean in it.
Slice thickly and cover with boiling water.
Return water to a boil.
Then remove and drain the meat.
Take a rolling pin and roll the meat until it is thin.
Dip the meat into cornmeal seasoned with black pepper and paprika.
Fry in shortening until golden brown.
A great accompaniment to any kind of greens.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil or slow cook the chicken until tender.
Pull apart into small bite size pieces. Spray casserole dish with nonstick spray. Layer chicken in dish.
Top with soup.
Finish with layer of stuffing mix.
Heat in oven at 350° for about 20 minutes or until hot.
tags: cream of chicken soup (cream of celery

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter; add peanut butter and cream again.
Gradually add sugar, egg, milk and then flour, baking powder and salt (already sifted).
Mix into a dough.
Roll into a thin dough and cut with floured cookie cutters.
Place in buttered pan and sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake in hot oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add milk and butter which have been heated to boiling point.
Beat well (do not add any more flour/batter to be thick).
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosty freeze pie
directions: Combine first two ingredients on medium speed.
Add next ingredients and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and freeze.

title: danish pastry
directions: Mix together with a fork.
Round into a ball and divide into two.
Pat dough into 2 long strips, 12 to 13 inches in length and about 3 inches wide on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: best banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Combine all ingredients into large bowl and mix well.
Transfer to prepared pan.
Bake until top is golden brown and splits slightly, about 1 hour and 20 minutes (start checking after 1 hour).
Can be served warm.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients, then heat enough to melt sugar.
Add pineapple juice and freeze.
Remove from freezer and partially thaw.
Take knife and chop up slightly.
Add 1 quart ginger ale before serving.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa and sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil one minute.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal, vanilla and chopped nuts. Mix all together and drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Use long, flat baking dish. (3 qt.)
Combine rice, water, bouillion cubes, onion soup mix and almonds.
Add green peppers. Season chicken pieces with salt and pepper.
Arrange the chicken pieces.
Top with the Mushroom soup.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Put in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, flour and milk.
Cook over low heat until it thickens. Take off heat; add cheese and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites.
Add to broccoli.
Fold in egg whites.
Put in one-quart dish.
Bake one hour.
It is done when knife is put in souffle and comes out clean.
Real good.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients. Cook over medium heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, soups and mushrooms.
Make a thin pancake batter and pour on the mixture in a glass cake pan.
Bake until brown in 325° oven.

title: clam-filled lasagna rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine reserved clam liquid and spaghetti sauce.
Reserving 1 cup sauce, spoon remainder equally into 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, combine clams, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, egg and parsley.
Mix well. Spread equal portions on lasagna strips; roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place seam side down in baking dish.
Top with reserved sauce.
Cover.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until hot.

title: frozen citrus pie
directions: Beat concentrate in a large mixer bowl about 30 seconds. Blend in ice cream. Fold in whipped topping until smooth.
Freeze, if necessary, until mixture will mound. Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 10 minutes before serving. Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: beer batter waffles
directions: In large bowl combine flour, sugar and salt.
Melt butter and let it cool.
Add all remaining ingredients, including butter, to flour mixture all at once.
Beat until smooth.
Set batter aside (at room temperature) and let rest for at least 1 hour before baking.
Stir batter gently before using.
Bake as directed.
Top with fresh fruit and whipped cream.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour in pan.
Do not stir in with oleo.
It will be thick and hard to pour.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Can add grated Cheddar cheese to mixture, if desired.

title: pistachio-pineapple salad
directions: Empty pudding mix into bowl. Add 4 tablespoons of the reserved pineapple juice and stir. Add pineapple, marshmallows, nuts and Cool Whip. Mix well. Chill. Serves 6.

title: corn pancakes, waffles
directions: Blend ingredients.
Batter will be slightly lumpy.
Bake on hot griddle or waffle iron.
Griddle is hot when a few drops water dance on surface.
Turn pancakes when bubbles appear and edges begin to dry.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes or three 7-inch waffles.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix together and cook in pan for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Put in containers and freeze.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix everything together & bake in greased 8 X 8 pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: almond meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add skim milk powder; mix well. Add extracts and sweetener.
Drop by spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes.
Dust with cinnamon.
Makes 12 cookies.

title: quiche pie(spinach or plain)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix in the order above in large bowl (mix by hand).
Pour into large 2 1/2-inch to 3-inch deep casserole (Pam oil spray) and bake for 1 hour or until center isn't watery.
Cool 10 minutes and serve.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Line muffin pan with foil cups.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar, and vanilla together.
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Optional:
Top with cherry, strawberry, or blueberry pie filling.

title: apple muffins
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Add milk, soda, salt and vanilla.
Alternate with flour, beating well after each.
Fold in apples, cinnamon and pecans.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar combined with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: tenth cloud cornbread(for those who cannot eat cornbread.)
directions: Stir gently; do not overbeat.
Bake at 425° until top is golden brown.

title: lemonade pie
directions: In a large bowl combine the thawed lemonade and condensed milk.
Stir until completely blended.
Add Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Food coloring may be added.
Pour into pie shell and chill.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: lemon mustard chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place chicken in a shallow pan.
Melt margarine and stir in mustard, lemon juice, tarragon and salt. Pour mixture over chicken breast and bake for 45 minutes or until cooked to desired taste.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, creamed corn, Carnation milk, eggs, salt, baking soda and bacon grease.
In large baking pan, pour 1/2 corn bread batter, then layer the remaining ingredients.
Pour the remaining corn meal batter over this and bake in 350° preheated oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1 cup of sugar.
Spread over pretzels. Mix jello, boiling water and strawberries.
Pour over top of Cool Whip mixture and chill.

title: jello salad
directions: Boil pineapple.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Add buttermilk and chill.
When mix is starting to set, add Cool Whip. Chill until firm.

title: pickled melons
directions: Fill jars with
melons (cantaloups) and set aside until syrup is made.
Pour off
all
juice
that has formed in jars. Heat sugar, water and
vinegar.
Fill
jars
with
syrup
and process 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not use overripe melons.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Boil chicken breasts and debone.
Lay in bottom of casserole. Heat soup and milk; pour mixture over chicken.
Prepare stuffing and place on top of chicken.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandmother stantons chocolate cake(made with coffee)
directions: Note:
When using bread flour, use 2 tablespoons less.
When using margarine, add a little salt.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in sugar, vanilla and egg yolk. Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, beating good after each 1/2 cup.
Chill 1 hour or overnight.
Roll and cut. Bake at 350° for 7
to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: mandarin snowflake delight
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix for 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack and cool.
Transfer to serving platter.
Frost top and sides with frosting.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: orange cookies
directions: Cream sugar, Country Crock margarine and eggs.
Add orange juice and rind, mix well.
Then add rest of ingredients with buttermilk.
Drop by spoon size on greased cookie sheet.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown meat in a skillet until the pink is gone.
Add other ingredients.
Cover the skillet with a lid tightly.
Turn to low and cook for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice thin and bake in hot oven (400°) for 8 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, peanut butter, cream cheese, and sugar.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry pretzel salad dessert
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with crushed pretzels.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 7 minutes in oven at 375°.
Cool completely.
Beat sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over cooled pretzels.
Mix 2 packages Jell-O with 3 cups hot water until dissolved.
Stir in partially frozen strawberries.
Pour over creamed mixture.
Chill until Jell-O is solid.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling, salted water until tender; drain. Arrange broccoli in greased 12 x 8 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Mix with rice and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and oleo; sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated.
(Serves 6.)

title: quick potato soup
directions: Bring hash browns, onion and chicken broth to a slow boil. Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir in cream of chicken soup and milk.
(I usually put in 1 cup of milk at first.
It just depends on how thick you like your soup.)
Salt and pepper to taste.
I also add a little garlic salt to give it flavor.	Let mixture simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with grated cheese, chives and real bacon bits.

title: cheesy crescent rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla together well. Spread 1 can of crescent rolls flat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crescent rolls.
Cover with 2nd can of crescent rolls.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients together (except pie shell).
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: quick pineapple salad
directions: Place everything except pineapple chunks, egg whites and marshmallows in pan and cook until thick.
Pour over pineapple. Let cool to lukewarm.
Add marshmallows and egg whites.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce rather fine.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add layer of drained peas.
Add celery and onion. Ice with mayo.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Sprinkle cheese over sugar. Cover with plastic wrap.
Make up one day ahead.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add second 4 ingredients.
Stir well, then spoon onto cookie sheet. Let cool.

title: candied pecans
directions: Mix together sour cream and sugar.
Cook until soft ball stage or 238°, stirring constantly.
Take off of the heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Stir well.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Cool.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix well and pour into oblong pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Bring sugar, Karo and water to a boil until a soft ball forms in cold water and a slight thread forms a spin from the spoon. Pour 1/3 slowly into beaten egg whites, beating constantly. Continue beating for a few seconds, returning syrup to a slow flame.
Add syrup to egg whites at intervals, making 4 intervals. Add vanilla and nuts.
Continue beating until mixture holds its shape when dropped from a spoon.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.

title: buttermilk caramel icing
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, butter, buttermilk, baking soda and salt in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Set in a larger pan of cold water; let stand until cool.
Add vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy, adding a small amount of milk or reheating for a short time, if necessary for desired spreading consistency.

title: tutti-frutti salad
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, drained oranges, fruit cocktail, coconut and lemon juice. Sprinkle pudding over fruit and toss lightly. Add bananas and walnuts. Chill.

title: tequila dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well (by hand or in blender). Cover and chill overnight.
Serve with taco chips that are thin and crispy.

title: shrimp dip 2
directions: Mix and serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: fruit kabobs
directions: Wash all fruit.
Drain pineapple but save juice.
Cut apples into chunks.
Remove stems from strawberries.
Peel and slice bananas.
Dip apples and bananas in pineapple juice to keep from turning dark.
Place fruit on wooden skewers.

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayo, pineapple, milk, ketchup, sugar, poppy seeds and Worcestershire sauce. Place coleslaw mix in a large bowl; add dressing and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: dilly green beans
directions: Stem beans, pack in hot sterile jars;
add pepper, garlic, sprague of dill;
heat water, salt and vinegar to a boil.
Pour over beans and spices in jars;
seal in a hot water bath:
when done put jars in corner away from drafts;
cover with a towel.

title: wintergreen cake
directions: Dissolve candy in milk.
Cream the sugar and margarine together.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and candy mixture; mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: polka dot chowder
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Barely cover with water.
Cook until done.
Do not drain.
Add sliced hot dogs, can of corn and onions. Reheat, then add milk and heat.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, celery and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Add to broccoli.
Mix in mushroom soup and the cheese; cook over low heat until cheese is melted and well blended.
A squeeze of lemon juice helps to retain the nice, green color.
Serve in a chafing dish with Doritos, Fritos or toast rounds.
This can be prepared ahead of time, but do not heat until the last minute.
May also be frozen.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Put in a buttered casserole dish.
Cook about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream tortillas
directions: Brown all of the above together.
Then warm together 16 oz. sour cream, 2 cans cream of chicken soup and 1/2 can green chilies.
In a 12 x 14 pan, pour 1/4 of sour cream mix.
Fill tortillas with ground beef mixture and put into pan.
Pour remaining sour cream mixture over the tortillas.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Serve with picante sauce, optional.

title: easy brown rice
directions: Combine rice and all soups in casserole dish; add mushrooms which will rise to the top when done.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: evelyn's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use as a dip for Boise potato chips.

title: kolaches
directions: Combine flour, sugar and butter with pastry blender until crumbly.
Place biscuits on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread out with fingers and indent middle slightly to hold filling.
Place 1 heaping tablespoon filling in each center.
Sprinkle crumbs over filling and biscuit.
Bake according to directions on biscuit can. Makes eight servings.

title: vegan angel biscuits(yield:  24)
directions: Add lemon juice or vinegar to soy milk and let stand 5 minutes.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in water; add with soy milk to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out on lightly floured surface.
If necessary, add more flour to make a soft dough.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted margarine and fold over to make pocketbook rolls.
Make the top portion larger so that when baked, top and bottom will be the same size.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
The dough does not need to rise at all before baking and may be stored in refrigerator before shaping and baking.

title: meat loaf on the go
directions: Mix raw ground beef and rice with your hands.
After well mixed, add sauce a little at a time until well mixed in.
Take mixture and shape in a loaf.
Place in glass baking dish and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nine-fruit medley
directions: In large bowl, combine the fruits; fold in yogurt. Just before serving, sprinkle with granola. Yield: 12 servings.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter baking dish.
Cook broccoli. Drain well.
Mix cheese and broccoli.
Put in prepared baking dish.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add molasses and egg.
Beat well. Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls; dip into sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate 370° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: scotcharoo squares
directions: Heat Karo and sugar in saucepan over low heat; stir frequently.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth, then pour over Rice Krispies in a large bowl.
Mix well, then pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pack it down smooth.
Melt chocolate chips in microwave; stir every few seconds (prevents burning), then spread on squares. Melt butterscotch bits in microwave, then spread on squares.
Let stiffen, but cut squares before completely hardened.

title: kristy's apple surprise
directions: Wash and core a small apple.
Fill with peanut butter or peanut butter and raisins or peanut butter and pineapple chunks, topped with nuts.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine ingredients into large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into decorative bowl.
Chill.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Leave in pan and make holes.
Cook pineapple and sugar until all water is out.
Spread over cake hot. Cool.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Spread pudding over cake. Then spread Cool Whip over as you would frosting.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans over top.
Refrigerate.

title: no stir vanilla pudding
directions: Put 2 cups milk in medium saucepan.
Add sugar; do not stir. Turn burner on medium-high; bring to a rolling boil.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line pie pan with crust.
Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar gradually; continue to cream until light and fluffy.
Stir in slowly syrup, honey, eggs, vanilla and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into crust; arrange remaining nuts on top.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in 350° oven; cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter the sides of a heavy pan.
Mix together 2 cups sugar and milk, stirring continuously until it reaches 234° (soft boil on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and let cool.

title: spiral salad
directions: Cook
spirals until almost done (10 minutes); rinse and drain. Pour Wish-Bone dressing over spirals while still warm. Sprinkle Salad
Supreme
and
Good Seasons over spirals;
mix well.	Add chopped
tomatoes, onion, pepper, olives and mushrooms; mix
well. Chill
overnight.	Let sit out a short time before serving.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions; cool.
In punch bowl or large salad bowl, crumble 1/4 of the cake.
Drizzle with Kahlua. Spread with pudding.
Add brickle and Cool Whip.
Repeat until ingredients are gone, about 3 or 4 layers.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix fruit and marshmallows.
Prepare fruit dressing.

title: b&b bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients and mix well. Store in covered plastic or glass container in refrigerator and use as desired.
Lasts up to 6 weeks, stored in the refrigerator. To use:
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full (use an ice cream scoop).
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice dish
directions: Brown chopped onion in a skillet with butter.
Boil Minute rice in water.
Mix all ingredients together and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 60 minutes or until rice thickens.

title: quiche lorraine with cheese and bacon
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain all but 1 tablespoon of fat. Crumble bacon.
Saute onion in bacon fat until soft.
Sprinkle Swiss cheese in pie shell evenly.
Add bacon and onion.
Beat eggs slightly, slowly beat in milk, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° for 15 minutes or until center is almost set but still soft (do not overbake, custard sets as it cools).
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup chocolate chips over.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla. Mix together lightly.
Combine dry ingredients; add slowly.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Lightly grease 9
1/2 x 11 pan.
Layer coconut and nuts. Pour prepared cake mix on top of this.
Cream together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar (blend with mixer until creamy).
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sunshine cookies
directions: Sift
flour,
baking
powder
and
salt
together.
Mix raisins
and nuts into flour.
Cream shortening and orange rind together;
gradually add sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Add egg
and
beat	well;
then add carrots.
Add flour mixture alternately with half and half, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Drop from a teaspoon on greased baking sheet, leaving 2 inch
space
between.
Bake
at
375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
6 1/2 dozen.

title: jean's pork roast
directions: Cover roast with mustard.
Place sliced onions in mustard. Place in pan.
Fill pan with 1/2 inch of water.
Bake for 3 hours in 350° oven.
Check occasionally to maintain water level.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Tear bread slices into pieces and toss in mixture until well coated. Add pineapple chunks and juice.
Toss together and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour in a 350 degree oven.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Add Cool Whip.
Layer pan with crackers.
Pour 1/2 pudding on top; repeat crackers and remaining pudding.
Top with crackers again.
Stir icing (heat in microwave if needed) until soft and spread over crackers.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken with mushroom sauce
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil and garlic.
Add soup, water and potatoes and cook for 45 minutes in covered Dutch oven.
Check for doneness by piercing leg with fork.
Add peas and salt and pepper. Serve when chicken in cooked and peas are hot.
May be served with rice or noodles.

title: lasagna
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven over high heat, cook ground beef and onion until beef is browned. Pour off pan juices. Add tomatoes, their liquid and next 8 ingredients.
Heat mixture to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Discard bay leaf.
Tilt pan and spoon off any fat which accumulates on top of sauce. Cook lasagna noodles as label directs. Drain well in colander.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, arrange half of drained noodles, overlapping to fit.
In a small bowl, combine eggs and cottage cheese.
Spoon 1/2 of this mixture over lasagna noodles in baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 Mozzarella cheese. Top with 1/2 of the sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 375° oven.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken divine
directions: Put broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then add chicken. Mix together soups, Miracle Whip and lemon juice.
Spoon over broccoli and chicken.
Top with shredded cheese and bread crumbs. Pour melted oleo over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll into the size of walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 3 ingredients; beat well.
Combine flour and other dry ingredients with egg mixture; beat well.
Add apples and pecans; mix.
Spread in well-greased pan.
(This is a thick batter.) Top cake with butterscotch chips; bake for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: slaw that keeps
directions: Shred the cabbage and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Squeeze out cabbage.
Boil the sugar, vinegar and water. Let cool.
Combine cabbage, celery and mangos which have been chopped.
Add seed and dressing.
Place in covered container and keep in refrigerator.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions; sprinkle with salt and cover with cracked ice.
Cover with a heavy lid; let stand 3 hours. Drain thoroughly and rinse well with cold water.
Place in a large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring almost to a boil, stirring constantly.
Do not boil.
Pack at once into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Process in hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 1/2 pints.

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: *Raisins may be steamed in water and drained.
This softens them.

title: googie butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix and margarine together and press into the bottom of a pan.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla, eggs and cream cheese. Pour over cake mixture and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Cool baked potatoes; cut in half and scoop out pulp. Melt butter in saucepan and add flour; stir until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and cook 1 minute on medium heat. Stir until thick and bubbly. Add crumbled fried bacon, potato pulp, salt, pepper, onions and cheese. Cook until heated. Stir in sour cream.

title: black forest mini cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line muffin pans with foil laminated baking cups.
Place one vanilla wafer on bottom of each cup.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, cocoa and flour; blend well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in sour cream and almond extract.
Fill each prepared cup almost full with cheese mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven; cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread heaping teaspoonful of sour cream topping on each cup.
Cool completely.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with dollop of cherry pie filling just before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 to 2 dozen cheesecakes.

title: sealed-with-a-kiss brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom and sides of an 8-inch square baking pan.
Reserve 16 kisses and coarsely chop the remaining kisses, about 1 cup; reserve.
In a medium bowl, beat the butter with an electric mixer until creamy.
Add the sugar and continue beating until mixture is light and fluffy.
Mix in the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in the chocolate and vanilla until blended.
Beat in the flour and salt just until combined.
Stir in the chopped chocolate kisses and walnuts.

title: tasty vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until done. Combine cheese, mushrooms and soup; heat. Pour cooked vegetables into 2-quart baking dish and pour cheese mixture over all. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together the pudding and pineapple.
