Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Chill.

title: early morning  toast
directions: Arrange bread in a single layer in a 13x9x2 baking pan.
In a medium bowl whisk eggs until blended.
Whisk in sugar, eggnog or buttermilk, cinnamon and butter.
Pour mixture over bread.
Turn slices to coat.
Cover with plastic wraps, refrigerate overnight. Preheat oven to 400° F. Bake 10 minutes.
Turn bread over and bake for 4 minutes or until golden brown in color.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter in an iron skillet.
Mix sugar, flour and cocoa; stir into oleo until well-coated and glossy or oily.
Beat egg yolks and mix with milk.
Add slowly to chocolate mixture.
Stir with a wire whisk and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dora's (grimm) cookies
directions: Mix as usual and add enough flour to make a good rolling dough.
Be careful not to add any more than necessary.

title: pizza for one(makes 1 serving)
directions: Grease ultra loaf cover; coat with cornmeal.
In small mixing bowl, combine biscuit mix and milk.
Stir just until mixed.
Pat into cover.
To bake, bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with remaining ingredients and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes more, until cheese melts.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until tender; drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of Cheddar cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and spread over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Trim with pimento strips.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: brazilian salad
directions: Toss all vegetables in bowl.
Combine sugar and cider; bring to boil to dissolve sugar.
Let cool.
Pour over vegetables. Store in refrigerator until vegetables are cool.

title: working girls' cake
directions: Mix with spoon in a large bowl the flour, sugar and baking soda. Add the pineapple.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Melt butter in a large 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Add cocoa and milk.
Stir well.
Bring mixture to a boil; remove from heat.
Add confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces. Cook covered in salt until tender. Drain.

title: sweet baked pork chops
directions: Place chops in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top each pork chop with ketchup first, then brown sugar, onion and slice of lemon. Cover with aluminum foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
(Remove foil last 10 minutes.)
Mikey likes 'em!

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a large bowl, mix the next 4 ingredients and spread over crumbs.
Layer fruit over creamy mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.
If desired, design with chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; blend.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of batter into separate bowl; stir in 1/4 cup chocolate syrup.
Spoon batters alternately into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chocolate cool whip pie
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave until stirable.
Swirl it through softened Cool Whip.
Put mixture into pie shell.
Keep in freezer until a few minutes before serving.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and shape into balls with hands.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Dip balls with two tine fork or toothpicks into chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to harden.
You may want to chill the balls a while before dipping them.
Makes 70 to 100 balls.

title: great stuff
directions: Simmer and stir salt and water for 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Take salt off stove; pour in cornstarch and mix.
When cool, mix with hands.
When you model with Great Stuff, wet hands now and then to help keep it smooth.
You can roll out between 2 layers of wax paper and cut out stuff with a knife, etc.
To roll evenly, place between 2 flat boards.
Poke tiny holes in large objects to speed up drying.
When dry, paint with tempera and then coat with shellac or clear nail polish.

title: deviled halibut steaks
directions: Mix the mustard, oil, chili sauce, horseradish and salt together.
Spread half of mixture on halibut steaks.
Put on greased broiler rack and broil for about 6 minutes under medium heat.
Turn fish; spread with remaining sauce and broil for 5 or 6 minutes longer.

title: trifle
directions: Cut sponge cake into pieces and mix with fruit salad.
Pour liquid Jell-O into the bowl with the sponge and fruit.
Once set, pour custard on top.
Allow to set in fridge.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring sugar and water to boil, add cranberries and boil for 10 minutes.
Pour over apples and jello.
Place in refrigerator and let jell.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add jello to 1 cup of boiling water and mix with other ingredients except sour cream.
Pour half of the salad into bowl and let congeal.
Pour half of sour cream on top.
Mix remainder of sour cream with remainder of salad and pour on top.
Let congeal.

title: crunchy sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice mix according to package directions. Set aside.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl, then mix in milk.
In separate bowl, sift together 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to liquid and mix thoroughly.
Put 2 inches oil in heavy skillet.
Heat oil until very hot but not smoking.
Dribble batter into hot oil, moving in circle to build snail-like coil. Fry about 2 minutes on each side, turning once with big spatula. Keep warm in very low oven.
Makes 6 to 8 cakes.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Break up chocolate; put in a pan over low heat.
Add 2 tablespoons milk, 2 tablespoons sugar and instant coffee.
Cook, stirring, until chocolate is melted.
Beat the cream cheese and rest of milk.
Add chocolate mixture.
Blend in Cool Whip; pour into crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook onion in bacon grease for 5 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook, stirring, 5 minutes more.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: crockery ham
directions: Place ham on metal rack or trivet in slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.
Remove ham.
Pour off juices; remove rind. Score ham; stud with whole cloves.
In a small saucepan, melt jelly with remaining ingredients.
Remove rack and return ham to pot.
Spoon sauce over ham.
Cover and cook on high for 25 minutes basting ham often.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine first three ingredients in saucepan.
Boil two minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Stir in 10x sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and creamy.

title: strawberry whip topping
directions: Beat together until thick and serve on angel food, white cake or pound cake.

title: double chocolate crumble bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients
and add to egg mixture.
Spread in bottom of greased 13
x
9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Spread marshmallows on top and bake 3 minutes.
Cool.
Combine chocolate chips
and peanut butter.
Cook until melted.
Stir in cereal. Spread mixture atop cooled bars.
Chill.
Cut into bars.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat onion to 400°.
Cook ground beef and onion.
Drain. Stir in salt and pepper.
Pour in greased pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick.
Pour over hamburger mixture.
Bake 25 minutes. Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: zucchini salsa
directions: Finely chop zucchini, carrot, tomato, garlic, peppers and tomatillos (which have been husked and rinsed).
Dice onion. Rinse in a strainer under cold water and drain.
Combine all ingredients and season to taste.
Add more chile peppers for hotter salsa.
Let stand at room temperature at least an hour before serving.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with tortilla chips or use as a condiment.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Note:
You can substitute any meat, cheese or potatoes to your taste.

title: mama's crisp cucumber slices
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt in large pan, cover with ice cubes.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain and rinse with cold water. Combine cucumber mixture with sugar, vinegar and spices.
Heat to boiling point and simmer 2 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.
Cook in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 pints.

title: smoked sparerib tips and cabbage
directions: Cover spareribs well with water.
Add salt, onion, garlic and 1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper.
Simmer until meat is half done, about 1 hour.
Wash, core and quarter cabbage.
Drop into pot. Add peeled, halved white potatoes and more seasoning; cook until done, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, brown sugar and peanut butter.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour and baking soda and add to mixture. Stir in milk and vanilla.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour but not longer than overnight.
Shape into teaspoon-sized balls and roll in sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Gently flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on wax paper covered rack.
As soon as cookies are placed on wax paper, press 1 unwrapped candy into center of each cookie.
Store in airtight container and keep cool to prevent candy from melting.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar for 20 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time and continue beating.
Add flour slowly.
Mix in lemon extract and beat until well blended.
Fold in 7-Up.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Test for doneness.

title: nuria's paella
directions: Cut chicken in large chunks and saute in oil with chopped onion and garlic salt.
Add 1 cup water and heat to boiling.

title: jayde's strawberry pie
directions: Mix
sugar, starch and jello together well.
Pour into cold water.
Bring to a boil and cook until it starts to become thick. Remove from stove.
Pour strawberries into baked pie crust and pour mixture over top.
Chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: barbecue macaroni
directions: In large skillet, saute ground beef, onions, sweet pepper flakes, seasoned salt and pepper.
Add barbecue sauce, water and mushrooms.
Mix well, simmer 20 minutes.
Cook macaroni, add macaroni to beef mixture.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into one 8-inch graham cracker crust.
Chill and serve.

title: moon craters
directions: Butter 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cook corn syrup, sugar and 2 tablespoons of butter in saucepan over low heat for 5 minutes or until mixture comes to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Add cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Press firmly into prepared pan.
Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter and chocolate chips in a saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over cereal mixture.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Store in airtight containers.

title: peanut butter sighs(microwave)
directions: Place
peanut
butter
and
margarine
in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 2 minutes, until
margarine
and
peanut
butter
melts.
Blend together. Add powdered sugar, stirring to mix.
Press smoothly into
bottom of dish.
Place chocolate chips in a flat dish to melt on High for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Spread over top. Cool in refrigerator and cut into squares.

title: tater tot dish
directions: Lightly brown ground beef and onion.
Place on flat baking dish.
Add a layer of green beans, then a layer of Tater Tots. Beat chicken soup and milk with eggbeater.
Pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Cream of vegetable or mushroom soup may be substituted for the chicken soup.)

title: date-nut cake(not a fruit cake!)
directions: Cut up dates, cherries, candied pineapple and pecans; set aside.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Beat eggs and add dry ingredients and mix until well blended.
Add vanilla.
Next add the fruit and nuts and mix well.
Put into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for about 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti bake(serves 24)
directions: Break spaghetti into 3-inch lengths; cook in salted water.

title: shrimp over noodles
directions: Peel and devine shrimp; set aside.
Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot. Add green onions and next 3 ingredients.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add shrimp.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in soup and seasoning; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in yogurt (at room temperature) and serve immediately over hot noodles.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cake topping
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with instant pudding. Add whipped topping. Very good on yellow cake.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions and cook until tender.
Drain off fat. Add corn, soup, sour cream, pimento and seasoning; mix well.
Stir in noodles.

title: summer pasta
directions: Combine all ingredients other than pasta while pasta is cooking.
Drain pasta and place on individual plates.
Top with mixture.

title: fudge
directions: Melt butter in large heavy sauce pan. Add milk and sugar. Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla, chocolate morsels, marshmallow creme and nuts. Beat on medium speed of electric mixer for 8 minutes. Spread mixture into a buttered 9x13 in. pan. When cool, cut into pieces.

title: marie stiffler's white house pies
directions: Mix well together but do not cook.
Line muffin pans with pie crust.
Add mixture and bake at 350°.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix Dream Whip.
Add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Thicken strawberries with cornstarch; cool.
Pour strawberries over graham crackers.
Pour Dream Whip mixture over strawberries.

title: fudge
directions: Stir until well blended and smooth.
Pour into buttered pan (10 x 15-inch).

title: hot country cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup mix for each cup of hot water.

title: virginia sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a flat baking pan.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir lightly with fork to combine.
Add butter.
With pastry blender; cut in until mixture is coarse and crumbly.
Add sweet potatoes to flour-butter mixture.
Add cream and blend just until soft dough forms.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter until onions are clear.
Add juice from clams and spices; simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine flour and water; stir well.
Add to saucepan and stir until thickens. Add clams until heated through.
Serve over noodles.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy. Add next 5 ingredients; beat with mixer. Add chopped apples and nuts; mix with spoon. Pour into greased Bundt or loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve jello in the boiling water. Add ice cream by spoonfuls. Stir until melted and smooth. Blend in Cool Whip. Add fruit. Spoon into crust. Chill 3 hours.

title: rotel tomato chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Drain broth; save 2 cups.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Mix spaghetti, chicken and Ro-Tel tomatoes with onion and bell pepper. Stir well.
Add cheese.
Season to taste.

title: saute vegetables over rice
directions: Put water, Italian dressing and California Blend in a large saucepan.
Cook until vegetables are almost done.
Add the squash, zucchini, onions and tomatoes to vegetables.
Cook for 5 minutes more.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Combine egg, milk and bread.
Let sit a few minutes, then mix in food processor using a pulse-off procedure.
Combine with all ingredients.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs just before done.
Serves 6.

title: skillet supper
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Saute potatoes, carrots, green pepper and onion in drippings.
Add sausage; cut into 4-inch chunks.
Cover.
Heat until sausage is heated through. Remove to platter and top with crumbled bacon.
Serves 4.

title: tomato-rice meatballs
directions: Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup tomato juice, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 teaspoon oregano in a large bowl.
Mix until well blended. Shape into 16 balls, using 2 tablespoons mixture for each. Arrange in a single layer in a large skillet or shallow pot.
Stir sugar and the remaining oregano into the remaining 2 cups tomato juice and pour over meatballs.
Cover and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce to low and cook for 20 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 5 minutes longer.
Spoon sauce over meatballs 2 or 3 times.
Makes 6 regular or 16 buffet serving meatballs with sauce.

title: marinated cabbage slaw
directions: Mix vegetables in large bowl.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup oil over the vegetables.
Stir in and let set 30 minutes. Boil the vinegar, sugar, water and seasonings for 1 minute and pour hot liquid over vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Will keep in refrigerator quite a while.
Stir occasionally to marinate.

title: currant cookies
directions: Mix as for pie dough, cutting in shortening, then add fruits and last milk.
Roll on floured board to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut in any shape desired.
Dip in sugar. Bake on cookie sheet about 8 minutes at 375°.

title: michigan potato candy
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, powdered sugar, vanilla and coconut thoroughly.
Shape into desired balls.
Place in refrigerator or until very cold.
Roll candy balls in melted chocolate chips. Refrigerate until firm.
Makes about 48 candies.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Heat all ingredients except popcorn to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in popcorn. Pack into hand size balls. Set on wax paper to cool.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well; add to flour, soda and baking powder that have been sifted together.
Stir in coconut, pecans, oatmeal and diced orange slices.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 12 to 14 minutes; cool.
Store in closed container.

title: cooked carrots
directions: Add to carrot mixture.
Heat until hot at 400°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions.
Spread Miracle Whip over onions, sealing to edge of bowl; cover.
Chill several hours or overnight. Garnish with bacon and shredded cheese, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble crackers in melted margarine.
Spread almonds and cracker mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken chalupa
directions: In saucepan, combine chiles, soups, sour cream, onion and milk.
Cook over medium heat until smooth and creamy.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer half of the chips on bottom.
Cover with half of the chicken, half of the sauce and half of the cheese.
Repeat. You can use extra cheese or combine types of cheeses.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour or until brown and bubbly.

title: bavarian apple strudel
directions: Beat together oil, egg, water and salt.
Add flour while beating, until a firm dough which pulls away from bowl is formed. Knead several times until smooth and elastic.
Cover; let stand 30 minutes.
Cut with sharp knife into 2 equal parts.
Roll out each piece on floured cloth to 12 x 18-inch rectangle.
Brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle evenly with breadcrumbs.
Spread 4 cups apple on each portion, lengthwise down center of dough.
Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon rum, 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar, 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon, 2 tablespoons almonds and 2 tablespoons raisins.
Fold dough over apples on one side, then the other.
Slice rolls onto greased baking sheet.
Brush with melted margarine.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Cut each roll into 2-inch slices.
Serve warm or cold, sprinkled with confectioners sugar or whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 18 servings.

title: dry gelatin salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and dry gelatin in a large bowl.
Add nuts, pineapple, and oranges.
Put in serving bowl and refrigerate.

title: rachel's broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli 8 to 10 minutes in salted water.
Drain and chop.
Add all ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle crumbled crackers over the top.
Pour margarine over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken-n-crunchies
directions: Cook chicken, cool, debone and chop into bite-size pieces. Toss with butter, salt and pepper.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole and serve hot, warm or cold.
Serves lots.

title: cherry ice cream
directions: Mix 1st 5 ingredients, then add milk to fill line and make in ice cream freezer.

title: broccoli puff casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Bake one hour.
(Use 1 1/2 quart or 2 quart casserole dish.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix milk, peanut butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Prepare Cool Whip as directed on box.
Fold into mixture, saving some for top of pie.
Put into baked pie crust and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix, using milk instead of water and vanilla.
Bake in two layers.
Let cool and slice in two, making 4 layers.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Remove crust from bread and drain pineapple.
Mix eggs and sugar.
Blend in rest of ingredients.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet.
Mix other ingredients together. Pour over hamburger and simmer about 45 minutes to 30 minutes will do.

title: hot fried potatoes
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Cut potatoes into small cubes, skins included.
Chop onion and hot pepper.
Mix all together and put in skillet.
While cooking, sprinkle on paprika and chili powder. Also sprinkle on garlic powder according to your taste.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add vinegar and coloring; beat again.
Add dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter.
Add hamburg and brown well.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Cook mostaccioli noodles.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, arrange alternate layers of noodles, meat mixture and cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mustard-style potato salad
directions: Mix mustard, sugar and vinegar well.
Add sweet pickle relish and milk.
Pour over diced potatoes, onion and eggs.
Mix well. Let set overnight for flavors to blend.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Heat cola, cocoa and margarine to boiling.
Add xxx sugar. Beat, then stir in nuts.
Spread on cake.

title: pecan millionaires
directions: Melt caramels, butter and water in double boiler; add pecans. Melt together Hershey bar and paraffin in separate pan.
(Do not boil.)
Dip by tablespoon carameled pecans in chocolate mixture for coating.
Put on waxed paper to cool.

title: blueberry bread pudding
directions: In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, toss bread cubes and berries.
In medium bowl, beat together remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over bread cubes.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until knife inserted near center comes out clean, about 55 minutes.
Serve hot or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (whip egg slightly in milk).
Slightly toss together.
Cook at 300° about 30 minutes or until bubbly all over.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese and flour. Add butter and mix thoroughly. (Work with hands.) Mold 1 teaspoon dough around each olive. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: spinach with angel hair pasta
directions: Saute the mushrooms and garlic in olive oil.
Add fresh spinach and cooking wine; blend together.
Then, add the creamed spinach; blend and cook for about 30 minutes on low heat.
Cook pasta according to directions and drain.
Mix together pasta with spinach mixture; add Parmesan cheese.
Serve with French bread.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all together and bake in a heavy pot or Dutch oven, covered, for 4 hours at 250°.

title: "texas hash"
directions: Cook onions and celery in oil until yellow.
Add meat and cook until redness leaves.
Add tomatoes, spaghetti and seasoning; mix. Put in large oiled casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rhoda's scalloped apples
directions: Spray 9 x 12-inch baking dish with Pam (or use 2 dishes). Cream butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix flour and cheese.
Slowly add flour mixture to butter-sugar mixture.
Pour drained apples into dish.
Spread cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: coke cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coke to boiling point.
Pour this over flour-sugar mixture and mix well. In another bowl, add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Combine the two mixtures.
Bake in sheet cake pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Bake in tube pan at 350° until dark brown and pulls away from side of pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; reserve 2 cups of broth.
Remove chicken from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Place in baking dish.
Add 1 cup of broth to the 2 cans of soup and pour over chicken.
Melt the butter and add 1 cup of broth.
Add to stuffing and mix well. Spoon on top of chicken.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together graham crackers, sugar and shortening; pat down into 8 to 9-inch baking pan.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and eggs and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then cool. When cool, mix sour cream, vanilla and sugar and spread on top. Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serve cooled either plain or with fresh fruit topping.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Add corn syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring continuously.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Mix popcorn and sauce.
Bake on low setting in oven for 45 minutes. Break apart and cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and mix.
Make into walnut-sized balls and place on buttered cookie sheet.
Press down in crisscross pattern with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mariner dip
directions: Break crab meat into fine pieces.
Add cream cheese, minced onion and salt.
Add salad dressing and chopped dill pickle and mix well.
Serve with cracklin' crisp potato chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses; mix well.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.
Chill 1 hour.

title: mushroom, cheese chowder soup
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in the butter until onion is soft. Add chicken stock and cook until carrots and potatoes are tender. Add mushrooms and parsley at the last few minutes of cooking. Blend flour in cold milk and stir into soup.
Heat to bubbling and melt cheese into it.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat, then fry.

title: k c's arabian spice ring
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil, 1/4 cup of milk and extracts. Beat 2 minutes.
Add rest of milk and eggs; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tasty fruit salad
directions: Combine sour cream and cinnamon.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix. Chill lightly before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, beef and onion, drain. Stir together beans after draining half the liquid from each can. Add remaining ingredients and combine with mixture of meat. Bake 1 hour at 350°; covered for most of that hour.

title: stephanie's fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
You may add any fresh fruit (of your choice) or the salad may be made entirely with fresh fruit, when available.
Makes a nice treat.

title: garlic bread
directions: Soften butter.
Crush garlic; work garlic into softened butter.
Cut loaf of bread into 1 1/2-inch slices cutting through to within 1/2-inch from bottom.
Spread garlic butter on either side of each slice; press back into shape and spread top and sides with garlic butter.
Wrap in foil and bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Open foil and bake 5 minutes more.

title: pork roast
directions: Trim all fat from the roast.
Cut slits through the middle of the roast (deep).
Stuff with mixed chopped vegetables and olives.

title: peanut butter crunch eggs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Crush Rice Krispies.
Mix thoroughly and shape into Easter eggs.
Melt chocolate in a double boiler and dip eggs (one side; let stand then the other).
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate mallow squares
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips together in a double boiler.
Beat egg with powdered sugar and add to double boiler. Let cool slightly and add vanilla and marshmallows.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers and refrigerate.

title: walnut crunch
directions: Butter 15 x 10-inch jelly-roll pan.
In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat sugar, butter, salt and water to boiling, stirring often.
Continue cooking to 290° or drop test into cold water until thread are hard but not brittle.
Remove mixture from heat; stir in coarsely chopped walnuts and soda.
Pour at once into pan.
Spread top with melted chocolate and sprinkle with finely chopped walnuts.
Cool.
By hand, snap candy into small pieces.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients, then add egg, oil and milk (or water).
Pour into small greased casserole dish or 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Corn bread is done when toothpick comes out clean.
Serve with crock-pot chili.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Pour 1/2 cup servings of fruit cocktail in dessert cups. Sprinkle small amount shredded coconut.
Drizzle honey on top.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Rinse chops; salt and pepper to taste.
Flour lightly.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Dip pork chops in egg mixture, then roll in crackers.
Fry in oil until golden brown, turning once.
Remove chops and place on grill or broiler pan and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: islander turkey salad
directions: Finely chop pepper.
Combine with turkey and nuts.
Add mayonnaise and red pepper.
Mix well.

title: seafood corn chowder
directions: Drain crab, shrimp and clams, reserving juices.
Cut crab into 1/2-inch pieces.
Saute bacon, onion, green pepper in large pot or Dutch oven until bacon is crisp.
Add potatoes, reserved juices from seafood, wine, salt, black pepper and thyme.
Cover and simmer over medium heat about 20 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add crab, shrimp, clams, corn, milk and half and half. Simmer 10 minutes longer.
Do not boil. Garnish with sliced green onions.
Serves 6.

title: deviled beets
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add 1 cup of beet juice and mix well with all ingredients except beets.
Bring to a boil and pour over beets.
Let stand a couple of hours before serving.

title: 3 musketeers pie
directions: Bake and cool crust.
Cut candy bars into small pieces. Combine gelatin and cold water in saucepan; let soften 5 minutes. Add candy bars.
Heat slowly over low heat until candy melts. Remove from heat.
Stir in ice cream.
Place mixture over bowl of ice water, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens.
Pour into pie crust and chill 3 hours.

title: sandies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar; add vanilla and water. Stir in flour and pecans.
Chill dough for 4 hours.
Shape into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until light gold, about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and roll in confectioner's sugar.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix all ingredients except butter in large bowl.
Grease a large casserole dish and put in the mixed ingredients.
Pour melted butter over top and bake for 1 - 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown.

title: ham roll
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Shape into a roll and roll in chopped pecans.

title: dill pickles
directions: Scrub medium cucumbers with brush; pack into hot, sterilized jars.
To each quart, add 2 heads of dill, 1 piece of alum and 1 teaspoon mustard seed.
Fill jars with hot brine, made of the cider vinegar, water and coarse medium salt.
Seal jars.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat, onion, garlic salt and lemon pepper and roll into bite-size balls.
Brown in a small amount of oil and drain.
Mix preserves and barbecue sauce and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add meatballs.
Serve warm in a chafing dish.

title: spinach salad
directions: Saute chopped bacon and onion.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard, brown sugar, vinegar and pepper.
Bring to a boil and pour over spinach.
Mix well.

title: "my original" christmas salad
directions: Chill lime Jell-O and crushed pineapple until firm.
Spread with cream cheese, pecans, celery and salad dressing.
Chill. Chill strawberry Jell-O until syrupy.
Spread over Jell-O and chill until firm.
Use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix well.
Make biscuits 3/4-inch thick and brush with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: scotch eggs(makes 8 servings)
directions: Coat each hard-cooked egg with flour. Divide sausage into 8 equal parts. Pat one part sausage onto each egg. Mix bread crumbs, sage and salt. Dip sausage-coated eggs into beaten eggs. Roll in bread crumb mixture.

title: cream of wheat bread
directions: Pour in well-greased skillet.
Bake at 450° until light brown.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Slowly cook all ingredients, except carrots.
When vegetables are done, pour over cooked carrots.
Marinate overnight.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate swirled peanut butter squares
directions: In bowl, stir together flour and brown sugar.
Using pastry blender, cut in butter and 1 cup peanut butter until coarse crumbs form.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of 2 (15 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) jelly roll pans.
Bake in a 350° oven until browned.
Cool on racks.

title: 3-day easy coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Split into 4 layers. Mix 1 1/2 packages of coconut with sour cream and sugar; set aside 1/2 cup of the mixture for later use.
Spread the rest between layers.
Mix the 1/2 cup of mixture with whipped topping and spread on top and sides.
Sprinkle rest of coconut on top of cake.
Refrigerate for 3 days in an airtight container before cutting.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables into bite-sized pieces.
Mix all ingredients together and stir until vegetables are well coated.
Marinate overnight.
This can be served as a side dish or with toothpicks as an appetizer.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: grade school baked cheese sandwiches
directions: Make sandwiches with buttered bread and cheese.
Put in greased baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together and pour over the sandwiches.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dot's homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, sugar and shortening. Beat eggs and add.
Add 2 cups of flour with a mixer, then stir in enough flour to form a soft dough.
Knead on a floured surface until smooth and elastic.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch dish.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs until creamy.
Stir flour, baking soda and salt, then mix with chocolate chips.
Spread into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Heat 1/2 cup water, lemon peel, lemon juice, honey, ketchup, bouillon cube, salt and garlic to boiling.
Mix cornstarch and 1 Tbsp cold water, stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened. Pour into a saucer.

title: rice dressing
directions: Melt oleo in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook vegetables over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a large casserole.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: guacamole
directions: Reserve 2 avocado seeds.
Scrape insides of avocado hull.
Mix all ingredients and either add 2 seeds or 3 drops green food color to keep it from turning black.
Tightly cover and keep it under refrigeration until ready to use.
Yields 4 servings.
Serve on chopped lettuce.

title: spaghetti hot dish
directions: Break up spaghetti into 2-inch long pieces.
Cook spaghetti and drain well.
Mix egg and milk and put noodles in egg mixture.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mince onion very fine by slicing down and crossways.
Mix meat, eggs, tomatoes (cut up), onions, salt and pepper all together. Last, add cracker crumbs.
Place meat loaf in Pyrex loaf dish.
Add catsup on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: cheese balls
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix all together.
Roll into one large or two smaller balls.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: chili con queso
directions: Cube cheese.
Mix with picante and peppers.
Microwave for approximately 5 minutes, stirring several times.
Serve on or with tortilla chips.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss all ingredients.
Add Fritos and dressing last.

title: ponnukokur meopeyttum rjoma(icelantic pancakes with whipped cream)
directions: Beat together all ingredients and mix in the stiff beaten egg whites lastly.
Bake paper thin on a hot cast-iron griddle. Spread with preserves, jam or jelly and 1 tablespoon whipped cream.
Fold into triangles.
Serve with afternoon coffee or as dessert.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Beat eggs gradually into oil.
Combine dry ingredients; add alternately with zucchini.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla. Pour into 2 greased and lightly floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes; let stand 10 minutes.
Turn onto wire racks to cool.
Can be glazed with powdered sugar.
Serve.
